title: dirt dessert
directions: In bowl, soften cream cheese and blend in sugar.
In another bowl, blend milk and pudding until thick; add vanilla.
Blend both bowls together and fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos in Ziploc bag until almost fine to look like dirt.
Layer 1/3 Oreos, 1/2 mixture, 1/3 Oreos, 1/2 mixture and 1/3 Oreos.
Gummy worms can be put in between layers.

title: icebox vegetable salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Pour over vegetables.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps up to a week in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, 1 layer graham cracker crumbs, 1 layer pudding mix, 1 layer graham cracker crumbs and 1 layer pudding mix.
Top with milk chocolate cake icing.
Let get cold before serving.

title: spinach bread bowl(appetizer)
directions: Mix first four ingredients and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours to mix flavors.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll meat in flour and seasonings.
Cut into serving pieces. Combine vegetables, pour over meat.
Cover pan tightly and reduce heat to low and simmer slowly for about 1 1/2 hours.
Can be baked in a slow oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple into
an oblong baking pan.
Dump cherry pie filling on top of pineapple; sprinkle with nuts.
Top with dry cake mix.
Dot
the
top
with margarine, but do not stir. Bake at 350° until	toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place
cups
water,
chicken, mushrooms, carrots and onion in a
large pot and bring to a boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth and let each cool separately.
Discard
skin
and
bones; cut chicken into bite-size pieces
and
add
to
vegetable mixture.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Skim
fat
from
broth
and discard.
Stir in poultry seasoning,
salt,
pepper, lemon juice, hot sauce and garlic. Combine
1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons flour and remaining 1/2
cup water;
stir
well.
Bring
chicken mixture to a boil;
stir
in flour mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered for 35 minutes. Combine
the
remaining
1 cup flour and the baking powder.
Add milk,
stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter by small teaspoonfuls into boiling broth.
Cover, reduce
heat and
simmer 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.
This has about 258 calories per 1 1/2 cup serving.

title: banana nut bread muffins
directions: Mix vanilla, sweet milk, vinegar and sugar, then add eggs and butter.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a greased muffin pan for 20 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Crush crackers in blender until powdery.
Stir in eggs and corn.
Place in casserole and top with butter pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, rice, raisins, vanilla, milk and dash of salt.
Mix well and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 42 minutes.
Pudding will be loose in the middle when removed from the oven.
It will set as it cools.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa. Add eggs, vanilla, flour and melted oleo. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: supper in a skillet
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add tomatoes, water, onions and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Spread uncooked noodles over top of meat mixture.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Yield:
5 or 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Melt butter; saute onion.
Add flour and water; stir until boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Cheez Whiz. Put broccoli in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole pan; pour mix over. Separate eggs; beat whites until foamy.
Fold in yolks; fold into casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs.
Cover with dots of butter. Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cover and chill for 30 minutes; roll into balls.
Press with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (watch closely).

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Soak in salt water (ice water) for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix equal amounts of Crisco oil and vinegar.
Let soak for 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add to cucumbers and onions.
Chill an hour before serving.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg in a bowl; add milk.
Stir in dry ingredients until batter is like pancake batter.
Heat oil about 1 inch deep (400°).
Pour in hot grease in carefree design through a funnel.
You decide the size of each cake.

title: waffles
directions: Combine buttermilk with eggs.
Add dry ingredients; beat well at high speed (electric mixer) until smooth.
Stir in melted butter or margarine.
Makes 10.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together lightly.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings; 1 serving = 2 meats.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes with skins on for 15 minutes.
Cool and peel.
Boil brown sugar, oleo and water for 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over sweet potatoes and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: no-fail chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
These ingredients may all be mixed right in a cake pan, but I prefer to use a mixing bowl.
Be sure the vinegar gets on the baking soda.
Do not overmix.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with chocolate frosting of your choice.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved and sauce is smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook pasta just until tender; drain. In a heated serving dish, combine all the remaining ingredients. Add the hot drained pasta and carefully toss to coat well. If desired, sprinkle pasta with freshly ground pepper and additional Parmesan cheese.
I also like to add some cooked shrimp to mine for a main dish.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and wine together.
Pour over chicken; add mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Can put foil loosely on top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Mix in remainder of ingredients.
Simmer until ready for use.

title: snack mix
directions: Melt white chocolate in microwave.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour melted chocolate over mixture.
Turn until coated well.
Place on wax paper.
Let cool.
Store in zip bags or jars.

title: filled date cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Mix quick oats and flour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 items and pour into baking dish sprayed with Pam of buttered. Top with croutons. Drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients and alternate with carrots.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased tube pan.
Dust with powdered sugar or ice with butter icing when completely cool.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and put in casserole dish. Combine oleo, poppy seed and Ritz crackers and sprinkle on casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: flaming cheese (saganaki)
directions: Cut cheese in 3 wedges; place in shallow serving dish.
Brush cheese with butter.
Set oven to broil and/or 550°.
Broil with top 4 to 6 inches from heat until cheese is brown and bubbly (5 to 6 minutes).
Heat brandy until warm; pour over cheese and light immediately.
Squeeze lemon over cheese.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli on bottom of pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and put over broccoli.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix brown sugar and whipping cream in glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 8 to 12 minutes or until mixture boils.
Stir in oleo, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and let stand until firm.

title: one bowl layer cake
directions: Stir shortening in large mixer bowl just enough to soften. Sift dry ingredients 2-3 times.
Put over the Crisco.
Add about 3/4 cup of the milk and mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat eggs 2 minutes or more.
Add eggs and remaining milk; beat 3 minutes longer, scraping bowl and spoon often.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 greased pans (Crisco) and floured pans.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken madeira
directions: Place chicken breasts in large, shallow baking dish.
Combine wine with soups and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, 2 1/2 hours at 275°.
Sprinkle cheese over top and garnish with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: In large casserole, pour uncooked rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix soups, according to directions.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender.
Remove foil and allow chicken to brown.

title: hot dogs in barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and cook slowly, about 15 minutes.
Cook hot dogs and rice separately.
Put hot dogs in sauce and spoon sauce over individual servings of rice.
(I serve the hot dogs with only a small amount of sauce, so that any leftover sauce can be safely saved; it lasts for weeks refrigerated in a glass jar.)

title: shrimp spread
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add tomato soup and cheese; heat until cheese is dissolved.
Dice shrimp and add with remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: tomato sauce with ground beef(makes approximately 6 to 7 cups of sauce)
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy saucepan; add onion and saute over low heat, stirring until tender and golden, about 5 minutes.
Add the garlic; saute 1 minute.
In the meantime, brown the beef in a skillet, stirring to crumble meat; drain off fat and add to the onion mixture.
Add tomatoes, 2 cups water, tomato paste and all of the spices.
Heat over a medium-low heat to simmering.
Simmer uncovered over a low heat, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sauce will thicken as it cooks.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Separate biscuit layers; place on top.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil after 12 minutes.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Put all ingredients in a large boiler.
Bring to a boil on low heat and simmer for 20 minutes. Serve hot.

title: caleb's fruit salad
directions: Peel and cut fruit.
Mix together in bowl.
Add juice and toss to coat ingredients thoroughly.
You can substitute, add or delete any of the fruits according to personal likes or what is in season.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze in cups.
When ready to use, thaw to the slushy consistency.
Can be made ahead and kept in freezer.

title: brook trout(4 servings)
directions: Clean and wash trout.
Cut off the fins.
Leave the head and tail on.
Dip the trout in seasoned flour.
Melt 1/4 cup butter. Saute the trout in this until they are tender and nicely browned. Remove the trout to a hot platter.
Add to the drippings in the pan the butter.
Permit it to brown.
Pour it over the fish.
Serve them with lemon wedges and chopped parsley.

title: mom's oil cookies
directions: Beat eggs till fluffy, add sugar, oil and salt.
Add 1 cup of flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder at a time and beat in between till you have a soft dough.
I use about 5 or 6 cups of flour. The dough must be soft and easy to roll.
Roll into long strips about 1/4 inch wide.
Cut into pieces about 2 inches long,
then as you get ready to shape them, roll again.
You can make them into bows or small circles.
Bake at
350° until golden brown, not dark.

title: bohemian slaw
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Mix chili sauce with mayonnaise, then add to slaw mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl; cut in solid shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast.
Knead on board in towel until stiff enough to roll.
Roll out and cut biscuits; place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Keep frozen until ready to cook.
Place in preheated 400° oven frozen and bake for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: poorhouse cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and beat in egg.
Mix or sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter/sugar mixture, alternately with molasses.
Add chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: marty's meat roll
directions: Brown ground beef (may use a little onion if desired).

title: broccoli puff(this is terrific!)
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour and gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Stir in salt, lemon juice, onion and broccoli.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Beat egg yolks; add broccoli mixture and fold in egg whites. Put in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole; bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and flavoring.
Add beaten egg and mix until creamy.
Add nuts.
Roll into small ball and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325 to 350 until brown.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine.
Keep refrigerated until to be used.

title: christmas nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients over fruit and nuts.
Cream sugar with egg yolks, vanilla and butter.
Fold in egg whites, which have been beaten until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in fruit-nut mixture. Pour into greased and floured loaf tins, 2 to 4, depending upon size of tins.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Mix together in large saucepan milk, egg and pudding mix. Add rice and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Add raisins and stir in.
Spices can be stirred in or sprinkled on top of serving.
Serve warm or cold.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix and spread evenly on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: crispy raisin drops
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy; beat in egg and vanilla. Mix flour, salt and soda.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture. Stir in granola and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased or nonstick baking sheets.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before removing to wire racks to complete cooling.
Yields 3 dozen 2 1/2 to 3-inch cookies.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Baking time:
10 to 12 minutes.

title: swirled apple rings
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 12-inch baking pan (no glass pans).
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Set aside.
Cut Crisco into flour until crumbly.
Add mix and stir until dough leaves the sides of the bowl.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead until just smooth. Roll into a rectangle (3/16-inch thick).
Mix cinnamon and apples together.
Spread evenly onto dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll. Slice into 18 slices.
Place in baking pan on melted butter.
Pour sugar water slowly over apples.
Bake 50 minutes.
This will look like too much liquid, but crust will absorb it.
Serve with ice cream.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Place canned vegetables and hamburger mixture in bottom of baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and mix in Cool Whip.

title: quick chile
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together.
Drain the grease off. Add tomato soup, red beans and package of chili mix.
Simmer on low for 15 minutes.

title: chicken crunch casserole
directions: Crumble some cracker crumbs over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine soups, sour cream and chicken. Pour over crackers. Add additional crumbs over top of casserole. Put about 1/2 stick margarine over top of casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix 2 1/2 c. sugar and 3 c. water.
Add 1 can of orange juice and 1 can of lemonade.
Add 1 can pineapple juice.	Mix well.
Add 3 cups cold water.	Pour into (2) 9 X 13 pans and freeze.
Cut into 3 inch squares.
Put into freezer bags (one pan per freezer bag). Take one bag of cubes and add a 2 Liter bottle of pop.
(Makes 2 batches.)

title: sichuan pork fried rice
directions: Heat oil in 10 inch skillet over medium high heat. Cook pork in oil 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until brown. Stir in carrots, onion and bell pepper. Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp tender. Stir in rice and stir fry sauce until well mixed. Stir in bean sprouts. Cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until hot.

title: gluten free oatmeal muffins
directions: In a small bowl combine the oats and buttermilk. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

Preheat oven to 425F. In a large bowl combine the buttermilk and oat mixture, brown sugar, butter, egg, baking powder, baking soda, salt xanthan gum, and egg enhancer. Gently stir in flour and raisins. Scoop into 6 greased Texas sized muffin cups and bake for 20 - 25 minutes, until tops are light golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes on a rack, then turn out of pans to finish cooling. Excellent toasted with your favorite jam.

title: diet pasta and vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into small pieces and fry in small amount of butter.
Add tomatoes last.
When vegetables are done, add cooked pasta and stir well.
Serve with salad.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Mix with flour.
Drop this batter around the edge of a casserole.
Cover tightly and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Don't pack!
To add a hint of more color, stir 1 tablespoon minced parsley into the sifted dry ingredients or try cheese dumplings; stir in 1/4 cup grated cheese into sifted dry ingredients.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix together pudding, topping and pineapple with juice until well blended.
Stir in apples, peanuts and marshmallows. Refrigerate.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add sour cream; add flour in four parts.

title: mama's turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Stir well and add milk and eggs. Mash thoroughly with potato masher. Bake in 2-quart casserole. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture, then add oats and water.
Beat well.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 28 minutes.

title: rosie's beef cubes
directions: In glass dish with lid, combine all ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Very easy.

title: mexican beef pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate with half of the pastry.
Heat oil in skillet; saute onion and green pepper 5 minutes.
Add beef; cook until browned, stirring frequently.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce; cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Add olives. Turn mixture into pastry shell.
Roll out remaining pastry; cut into thin strips.
Arrange over meat in lattice pattern.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 35 to 40 minutes or until pastry is well browned.
Yields 5 or 6 servings.

title: kennedy beef
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Place in casserole.
Add pepper. Pour mushroom soup over meat.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Bake at 225° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir mixture.
Bake another hour. Blend in mushrooms.
Add wine.
Bake another hour.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread; put half in bottom of pan or skillet.
Put browned meat and cheese, then put other half of cornbread on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hobo bread
directions: Combine raisins, soda and water.
Let stand, covered, overnight.
In the morning, add oil, brown sugar, flour and salt. Bake in floured and greased loaf pan in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese together and pour on top.
Let stand in refrigerator for 6 hours.
Toss together before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Combine lemon juice, sugar and water. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add orange juice and pineapple juice. Mix well. Chill. Add ginger ale and sherbet. Makes 30 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix and drain green
beans, sweet peas, corn, pimentos, bell pepper, onions and
celery.
Mix
apple
cider
vinegar, water, oil, salt, sugar and black pepper.
Bring to boil.
Let cool. Pour over vegetables.
Make the day before serving.

title: french onion soup
directions: Place onion and butter in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook, covered, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add broth, water and Worcestershire sauce. Cook, covered, for 5 to 7 minutes.
Toast bread.
Place on paper towel.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with Swiss cheese. Heat for 15 to 30 seconds.
Place one slice of bread in each serving bowl.
Pour soup over bread.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: crab cheese toast
directions: Melt butter and add cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add crabmeat and stir until blended and heated throughout.
Heap on English muffin halves and place under broiler for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Drain liquid from oranges, add water to make 1 cup.
Make cake mix according to directions substituting liquid from oranges for water.
Chop oranges put into batter.
Mix. Bake in 3, 8 inch cake pans.
Cool.

title: zesty potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish.
Combine next 4 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Pour over potatoes, stirring to coat well. Spoon Cheez Whiz over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Spread in baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese with Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy and spread on cool crust.
Mix pudding with milk 3 minutes on low speed.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Refrigerate or freeze about 45 minutes before serving.

title: beef stew in the oven
directions: Put all into roasting pan and cover.
Bake 250° oven for 4 hours.
Stir several times during baking.
Do not brown meat. Cooking turns to brown gravy.

title: zuccotto mandorla
directions: Bake cake as package directs.
Cool and cut cake into slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle brandy and wine over cake.
Spread almonds in shallow pan and toast in 400° oven 5 to 8 minutes or until golden.
Whip the cream with sugar until very stiff.
(Place towel over mixture if it splatters.)
Fold almonds, chocolate and vanilla into cream.
Line a 3-quart round mixing bowl with foil and butter well.
Place about 3/4 of cake slices all around the side of bowl.
Fill bowl with whipped cream mixture and make a layer of the remaining cake on top.
Cover with foil and chill for at least 24 hours before serving.
Invert pudding from bowl; remove foil and sieve cocoa over top.
Sprinkle with finely chopped almonds.
Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecued brisket or beef
directions: Put brisket in foil wrap in shallow pan. Cover meat with mushroom soup and sauce. Sprinkle top evenly with dry onion soup mix. Seal foil. Cook in 350° oven 2 hours. Unwrap; slice against grain. Serve gravy over meat. Makes about 2 cups of gravy from this recipe. Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
Beat eggs and milk together. Add salt and beat again.
Add bread and stir until it softens. Stir in cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes and add next 4 ingredients. Heat at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with wheat crackers.

title: turkey 'n stuffing bake
directions: Combine butter and water.
Pour over stuffing mix and toss. Stir in 1/2 can fried onions.
Spoon into a 9-inch (1 1/2-quart) baking dish.
Press mixture across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Combine soup, milk, turkey and peas; pour into a shell.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour in casserole dish and add 1/2 stick margarine on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: steamed vegetables
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Set aside.
Add squash, zucchini and water.
Cover and steam with onion mixture for about 5 minutes.
Stir tomatoes into pan and heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon lemon pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over vegetables.

title: bean casseole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in a 9x13-inch baking dish.
Put 1 cup sharp cheddar cheese over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven barbecued beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place meat in baking pan and sprinkle liberally with salt, pepper, garlic and liquid smoke.
Roast meat about an hour.
Slice meat in the pan and arrange slices in one layer.
Pour barbecue sauce over the meat.
Cover tightly with foil and roast 1 hour longer.
Uncover, roasting until sauce is thick and meat nicely browned.

title: date walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and line bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with waxed paper and grease top of wax paper.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until light.
Add brown sugar and mix until smooth.
Gradually add dates, nuts and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Stir in dry ingredients; mix well.
Spread in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove to wire rack and remove wax paper.
With sharp knife, cut while still warm into about 24 pieces.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in small crock-pot.
Add chili, onions and black olives.
Cook until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate candy roll
directions: Melt chocolate and butter on low heat.
Cool slightly, then add powdered sugar and the egg.
Cool more and add nuts and marshmallows.
Spread coconut out on waxed paper.
Spoon out chocolate mixture on top of coconut.
Form rolls and sprinkle more coconut on top.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes, then slice and eat.

title: multi layered salad
directions: In a 4-quart clear salad bowl, arrange lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon peas, mushrooms, olives and zucchini in layers evenly over lettuce.
Arrange egg slices and bacon over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise and lemon juice; spread mixture evenly over top. Cover, refrigerate until serving time, at least 6 hours.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Add chicken breasts to boiling water with bay leaf, celery and onion.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken; allow to cool.
Save broth.
Cut tortillas and grate cheese; set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine green chilies, onion, soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Add enough broth to make about 1 to 2 cups.
Cube breasts. Assemble in casserole dish.
Pour small amount of sauce in bottom of dish, then layer of tortillas (several thick), layer of chicken and a few black olives.
Finish with cheese.
Repeat layers as necessary, ending with cheese.
Add dollops of sour cream; sprinkle with more black olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until heated through.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and congeal.
Mix 1/2 cup pineapple juice, sugar, egg and flour; mix well.
Cook over low heat until slightly thick; cool.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on jello.

title: farm dinner
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Pour onion over beef; add uncooked peas and soup, undiluted.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: pizza dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic.
Spread in the bottom of glass pie pan.
Top with pizza sauce, then green onions, then green peppers and cooked meat.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon pecans onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° until pecans are dry.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Blend well with a large spoon.
Serve room temperature or cool. This salad is very pretty.

title: okra, corn and tomatoes
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter.
Add tomatoes and cook about 10 minutes.
Add layer of okra, then layer of corn.
Do not stir at this point.
Cover with lid and cook about 20 minutes.
Remove lid and stir.
Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spread 4 cups potatoes in bottom of greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Pour half the mixture over potatoes. Repeat layers.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer.

title: holiday "dessert" pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease one 12-inch or two 9-inch pizza pans with butter or margarine.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for fudgy
brownies.
Stir chopped peanuts into batter. Spoon mixture into prepared pan(s).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes; cool in pan.

title: kolache cookies
directions: Bring margarine or butter and cream cheese to room temperature. Cream together. Add flour, powdered sugar and baking powder. Add additional flour if dough is too sticky.
Form into a roll. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: skinny fries
directions: Slice potatoes into a bowl of ice water.
Remove and pat dry. Spray a baking sheet with vegetable oil spray and spread the fries on this in a single layer.
Then sprinkle up to a total of 2 tablespoons salad oil over surface of potatoes.
Bake in 450° oven, turning often, for 30 minutes or until golden and tender.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Tear
spinach
in bite size pieces.
Slice water chestnuts. Break bacon into bits.

title: cupcakes
directions: Put raisins in water and boil for 10 minutes.
Then add oleo after raisins are cooked.
After raisins are cool, add rest of ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Mix altogether.
Boil until sheets off of a wooden spoon. Pour into sterilized jars.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain and mix eggs, mayo, salt, pepper, milk, cornstarch and olives in bowl.
Fold in cheese and hamburger mixture.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: texas trash
directions: Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Grease 12 large muffin tin cups or 12 custard cups. If using custard cups, place them in a shallow pan. Break the eggs into a bowl; beat well with a fork or whisk. Add the milk, flour and salt and beat until just blended. Fill the muffin tins or custard cups 3/4 full with the batter. Place the pan on a rack in the center of the oven. Set the oven to 450° and turn it on. Bake for 30 minutes without opening the oven door. Serve the popovers hot with plenty of butter, jam, syrup or honey.

title: healthy salad dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate before using.
A tossed or any type of green salad go great with a pasta meal, along with some good Italian or garlic bread.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese and seasonings.
In buttered dish, layer one-half of rice mixture; sprinkle with 1/2 cheese and 1/2 green chiles.
Repeat layer of rice, cheese and chiles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Chocolate chips, raisins or nuts can be added if desired.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Mix butter, milk, cocoa and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and stir in oats and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine until crumbly.
Pat mixture into bottom of 8 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix well. Add 1/2 Cool Whip and spread mixture over crust.
Let set up for 10 minutes.
Combine milk and instant pudding.
Pour over other layers when pudding has set.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with toasted chopped pecans.
Chill thoroughly and serve.

title: toddy
directions: Heat glass with some hot water.
Put brown sugar and hot water into glass.
When sugar has melted, add some of the whiskey, stirring well.
Then add more hot water and some more whiskey. Serve hot.
Traditionally served in a crystal glass and stirred with a silver spoon.

title: homemade marshmallows
directions: Put 1/4 cup cold water and the gelatin in a 2-quart saucepan; let soak together.
Warm together 1/4 cup water, 3/4 cup invert sugar and 1 1/4 cups sugar.
When sugar mixture is hot, but not boiling, pour into mixing bowl.
Add the soaked gelatin, corn syrup and vanilla.
Whip until white, fluffy and at least doubled in volume.

Pour into pan or molds sprayed with Pam; allow to set 24 hours (sometimes less) before attempting to cut or unmold. Shapes may be rolled in toasted coconut or dipped in melted coatings or colored sugars.

title: party pink salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice and marshmallows.
Place over low heat. Add gelatin.
Melt marshmallows and dissolve gelatin.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix. Fold in Cool Whip last.
Place in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.

title: all-chicken chili
directions: Combine onion, garlic and green pepper in a sauce pan.
Saute in very small amount of oil until tender.
Add remainder of ingredients and stir.
Remove to larger sauce pan.
Decrease heat to simmer and cook until desired thickness.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Blend together cream cheese, milk and sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture on cake, then spread on cherry pie filling.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Stir salt into milk; dip in fish fillets.
Roll
in	bread
crumbs and place in lightly greased baking
dish
x
9 x 2-inches).
Drizzle melted margarine over fish.	Bake in 500° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chili-ghette
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and brown garlic, onions and ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes and chili. Simmer about 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti and drain. Remove skillet from heat and stir in Cheddar cheese until melted. Fold in sour cream.
Combine chili mixture and spaghetti, mixing well.
Turn into 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: potato dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine potatoes, chilies and cheese. Mix well. Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes and apples, ending with potatoes.
Sprinkle each layer with some sugar, allspice, butter and lemon juice.
Bake 20 minutes or until nicely browned.
I like to add cinnamon and nutmeg to the sauce.
Serves 8.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Chop all ingredients finely.
Mix ingredients together.
Best made a day in advance.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Immediately mix in butter and soda.
Add egg, flour, nuts and sugar.
Mix and bake in a greased loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Stir in milk until batter is smooth. Dip rings into batter, then into hot oil.
Turn over when brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple with their juices.
Drain oranges well and add to pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and chill overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Slice squash into 1/4-inch circles.
In skillet, saute onion in hot oil until tender.
Add squash and spices.
Add tomato sauce over squash.
Cover and cook until tender (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Top with cheese.
Cover skillet and continue to cook until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in small bowl. Beat butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla in large bowl. Add flour mixture. Stir in oats, morsels and chips. Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crispy cookies. Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes, then place on wire rack to cool. Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add buttermilk.
Add soda, baking powder and salt, then meal.
Pour hot fat over it.
Cook at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: bruschetta
directions: Cut loaf in half lengthwise and then cut into 2-inch slices. Toast cut sides. Drain tomatoes thoroughly; chop tomatoes. Combine tomatoes with remaining ingredients. Spoon tomato mixture onto toasted slices. Broil 5-inches from heat source until tomato mixture is hot, about 2 minutes.

title: meatballs with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine thoroughly ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion, garlic salt and pepper.
Shape into 35 balls; chill 1 hour.
Over medium heat melt margarine.
Brown meatballs on all sides.
Drain fat.
Combine soup and water.
Add to frypan and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla strawberry parfait
directions: Cover the bottom of a small glass with a layer of yogurt.
Cover layer with strawberries.
Repeat layers until glass is full ending with strawberries.
Sprinkle with graham crackers and nutmeg.

title: pie crusts
directions: Use a large bowl.
Mix together 4 cups flour, the sugar and salt.
Work in the lard with a pastry blender or 2 knives, or your fingers until it is like coarse cornmeal.
You can use other shortening, but lard is best.
Do not use oil.
Slightly beat the egg.
Add the vinegar and water; mix these together and add to the dry mix, a little at a time, stirring with a fork.

title: old fashioned dressing
directions: Combine crumbs, onion, celery and seasonings.
Add margarine, milk, broth and eggs.
Stuff loosely into turkey cavity.
May spread into greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Stuffing for a 12 pound turkey.

title: middle eastern meat patties(makes 8 servings)
directions: Grate potatoes (drain all water from potatoes) and set aside. In a bowl, combine meat, egg, onion, potatoes, salt, pepper and turmeric.
Knead for 10 minutes to form a smooth paste.
Using damp hands, shape mixture into lumps the size of an egg.
Flatten and brown on both sides in a skillet in 1/2 cup oil over medium heat (making sure potato is cooked).
add more oil if necessary.

title: better then ever cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and bake.
Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
When cake is done, poke holes in cake and pour mixture over cake; let set.
Mix pudding; spread over cake.
Slice bananas, next Cool Whip, cherries and nuts next.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; let cool.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add frozen strawberries.
Chill in bowl, but do not let it set completely.
Mix cream cheese, then add 1 cup sugar, Cool Whip and drained pineapple; mix until well blended.
Pour over pretzels.
Spoon Jell-O mix over cream cheese layer.
Spoon crushed pretzels over top.
Let chill overnight.

title: pepsi roast
directions: Cook on low for 8 hours.
Stir all ingredients before adding roast.

title: low carb ice cream
directions: Whish eggs whites until soft peaks form.
In a separate bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth (heat in a microwave for 10-15 seconds to soften first).
Mix in cream, egg yolks, vanilla and splenda.
Fold in egg whites.

title: blueberry sour cream loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Lightly beat egg in a mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, milk, almond extract and muffin mix.
Stir just until blended.
Fold in pecans.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: hershey's chocolate-banana snacking cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, banana, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour batter in ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool with whipped topping, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: husband's delight casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix onions, cream cheese and sour cream.

title: berry crumble(microwave)
directions: Place berries in microwave-safe 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread on berries. Microwave, uncovered, on High 7 to 10 minutes, or until berries are hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Cook sugar cookie dough on pizza pan until done. Cool cookie. Spread sour cream onto cookie. Place sliced strawberries onto sour cream. Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Cube chicken breast into bite size pieces.
Dice bell peppers and onions.
Saute chicken, peppers, and onions together in oleo until chicken is white and the onions are lucid.
Add broth, salsa, and corn, bring to a boil, and let cook for 10 minutes. Add rice and cook until liquid has been absorbed.
Turn off heat and sprinkle top with cheese.
Cover with lid, let stand until cheese melts from the steam.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Stir together broth, soup, onion and chili peppers in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Alternate layers of tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with green onion and tomatoes.
Serves 6.

title: maritza's bean dip
directions: On a dip dish, layer the refried beans, salsa, sour cream and cheese. Layer some black beans, lettuce, chopped tomatoes, onions, black olives, avocado, cilantro and peppers. In the center, place a small amount of sour cream, cilantro and olives.

title: cornstarch modeling mixture
directions: Mix salt, cornstarch, water and color in pan.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is too stiff to stir. When cool, knead until smooth.

title: baked duck
directions: Rub ducks with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper. (Small amount of garlic powder can be added if desired.)
Put duck, breast down, on piece of aluminum foil.
Put some chopped mushrooms on top of duck.
Wrap duck tightly in foil and bake, breast down, in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: chicken fettuccine casserole
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 1 hour.
Cook fettuccine, peas and carrots until tender in 1 big pot.
Cut up chicken in in small pieces.
Drain noodles, peas and carrots.
Place noodles and vegetables in casserole dish (11 x 13-inches).
Mix chicken through the noodles.
Pour 2 cans of cream of chicken soup over casserole and mix through.
(Add a little water to soup to rinse out can.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; reserving juice.
Combine margarine and flour in saucepan, cook until bubbly.
Add reserved juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Layer asparagus, cheese, almonds and sauce in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: seafood fancy
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until hot through and crumbs are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spring garden pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water in a large saucepan until tender, but firm.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Spray with Mazola nonstick cooking spray.
Combine pasta and remaining ingredients except dressing in a medium size bowl.
Pour dressing over salad. Toss and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all vegetables in bowl.
Mix sour cream and mayo together and top over vegetables.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk with sugar and shortening; cool to lukewarm.
Then add yeast dissolved in the warm water.
Add the flour.
Let rise until double in bulk and then add salt, soda and baking powder. Add additional flour (about 1 cup) to make a soft dough.
Place in bowl.
Grease surface of the dough and cover and place in refrigerator.
Make rolls as wanted.
Take out amount needed and let rise.
Rolls will last a week or ten days.

title: chocolate drink mix
directions: Mix ingredients and store in airtight container.
Mix 2 heaping teaspoonfuls with 1 cup boiling water.

title: oat cakes(from nova scotia)
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Add rolled oats (either kind).
Cut in shortening or margarine.
Add enough cold water to mix.
Roll out in graham flour or regular flour, if you prefer. Cut into squares.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: messy tomatoes
directions: Dip tomatoes in flour; fry brown on both sides.
Put all fried tomatoes back in skillet.
Stir and add milk slowly; stir constantly, adding milk until it becomes gravy.
Serve with ham and biscuits.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour together real good.
Add milk.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Cook until thick; add oleo and vanilla. Add to wafers and bananas.
I use about 1/2 box wafers and 3 or 4 bananas.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vinegar, mustard and butter or margarine. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Grate onion and cheese; mix together. Chop pimentos and add.
Pour cooked mixture over cheese mixture and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: blt salad
directions: Dressing:
Blend together buttermilk, mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, basil, oregano, and garlic powder.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, oleo and chocolate chips.
Pour over Chex cereal.
Toss lightly.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Mix with rubber spatula, being careful not to break Chex.
Spread on cookie sheet to dry.
Serve as a snack to people, not puppies.

title: burnt sugar cake(dad's favorite birthday cake)
directions: Burn sugar, then add water to make burnt syrup.

title: open-face ham sandwich
directions: Spread mixture on muffins and top with an additional cheese, if desired.
Place under broiler until it is hot and bubbly.

title: macaroni-squash stew
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, drain and set aside.
Saute garlic and onion in Crisco oil.
Add stewed tomatoes, salt, pepper and basil; bring to a boil.
Add cut up squash and saute, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add sugar.
Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift the first	4
ingredients	together
and mix well. Add the beaten egg,
sour
cream, vanilla
and	nutmeg, mixing well. Fold mixture into apples carefully.
Spoon all into pie shell. Bake at 400° for
minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.
Take
pie	from
oven.
Have
topping ready to put on pie.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Cream together first oil, sugar, then eggs and pumpkin.
If you use self-rising flour, omit soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into large greased and floured cookie sheet or pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Grease casserole dish; drain corn (white and whole).
Mix together in dish all corn.
Mix in a separate bowl, remaining ingredients, excluding butter.
Add to corn; slice butter on top. Bake at 400° until bubbly, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: rotel casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain well.
Place crumbled nacho chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with hamburger.

title: sunset soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium high heat, cook onion and green pepper in butter or oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir often.
Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Saute onion until golden; set aside.
Brown meat in hot oil. Do not crowd.
Do in two batches if skillet not large enough.
Put browned meat in pot.
Cover with cold water; add onion and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Pepper to taste.
Mix soup mix with 1 cup cold water and 1 tablespoon flour.
Add to meat; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add more water or beef stock if getting too thick.
Squeeze garlic through garlic press.
Mix into stew the last 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mary's chicken casserole
directions: Mix well (except noodles).
Put in casserole.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and spices.
When boiling, drop in cucumbers and onions and boil 2 1/2 minutes.
Put in jars.
Cover with juice; seal.

title: pecan pie crust
directions: Mix into bowl sugar, cocoa, cinnamon and salt.
Spoon dry mix onto half the pie round; do not overfill.
Pat each with margarine.
Fold over and flute edges together well with fingers. Fry in iron skillet over low heat until golden brown.
Turn over gently and fry other side or bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: taco-hamburger casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, chili powder, salt, onion and garlic.
Cook 7 minutes and drain.
Layer as follows in 9 x 12-inch baking dish: 3 to 4 taco shells, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 corn, 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This will freeze very well.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Lightly salt the zucchini and let stand for 15 minutes; squeeze out excess moisture.

title: cheese sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Put all in crock-pot on low.
Turn up to high when cheese starts to melt.
Stir occasionally until all melted and hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix salad dressing mix, oil and seasoning.
Pour over crackers in bowl.
Shake gently until crackers are covered.
Cover plastic bowl.
Turn over periodically.
Enjoy!

title: easy cake batter
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, egg yolks and flour.
Separately mix soda and buttermilk.
Then add the buttermilk mixture to the flour mixture and mix until smooth.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, or until brown/done per touch test.

title: vegetables romano
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes. Continue cooking over low heat 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Romano.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef and drain any grease from meat.
Open box of Rice-A-Roni and take flavor packet; set aside.
Add contents of box to meat and continue to cook until rice has browned.
Pour in 3 cups water and can of tomato sauce.
Add flavor packet and chili powder.
Turn heat down on low and cover skillet.
Simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: basic white bread
directions: In large bowl, mix 2 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Add 1 1/2 cups warm water and oil.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups more flour.
Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 8 to 10 minutes.
Spray with vegetable spray, cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Place in casserole.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Spread over casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coffee ring
directions: Place ring of walnut halves in greased round pan.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Place in pan, overlapping slightly.
Tuck raisins between biscuits.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in bite size pieces.
Slice onion and slice the potatoes, but not too thin.
Butter a large casserole dish or oblong baking pan.
Place a layer of cabbage, a layer of potatoes and a layer of onion; then repeat.
Pour melted oleo over layers, then salt and pepper.
Put tinfoil over top and place in a 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove foil and lightly brown.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Combine ketchup and sugar in crock pot on low heat and set aside.
Slice package of bacon into thirds.
Wrap bacon around hot dogs.
Hold together with toothpick.
Broil 1-2 minutes in over to crisp bacon, turning once.
Put broiled dogs/bacon into crock pot 2 -3 hours on low.

title: starlight mint cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, eggs, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in soda, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: red pepper and corn relish
directions: Roast red pepper over gas flame or under broiler until blackened on all sides.
Seal in paper bag and let stand 10 minutes.
Peel, seed and chop red pepper.
Combine vinegar, syrup, Tabasco sauce, turmeric and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually whisk in oil.
Add red pepper, corn and green onions and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate overnight, stirring occasionally.
Can be made 3 days ahead of time.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt water until tender.
Drain and add all ingredients except margarine and dressing cubes.
Add dressing cubes to margarine.
Pour half of cubes in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Add squash mixture.
Top with cheese slices.
Add remaining dressing cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crisp diet chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix
salt,
pepper
and	paprika with crushed cereal.
Dip chicken
in
skim
milk
and roll in crushed cereal mixture.
Spray foil lined pan with Pam or corn oil and add chicken pieces in one layer.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake
about
minutes more until chicken browns.

title: pound cake cobbler
directions: Cut pound cake into 1-inch cubes.
Place cubes in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole or a 9-inch pie plate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
Cook until blended.
Mix with thawed broccoli and rice.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pasta salad(make day before)
directions: Mix all ingredients except rotini.
Mix well using whole bottle of salad seasoning, then add rotini.
Mix very well and chill, stirring every hour or so until chilled so all the pasta gets seasoned.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together except raisins and nuts.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Add raisins and pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter supremes
directions: Mix shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars; mix well.
Beat in eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients and stir in.
Make dough into small balls.
Roll top in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mama's cereal(snack mix)
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels and crackers in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Mix lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and powders.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Cover cereal completely. Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes more.
Stir and cool.

title: cheese ball #2
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with pineapple, 1 cup pecans, bell pepper,
onion
flakes
and seasoning salt.
Roll into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll the balls in the remaining 1 cup pecans.
Top with a cherry and serve with crackers.

title: dieter's delight casserole
directions: Boil macaroni; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle with corn flake crumbs.
Bake casserole dish at 300° for 30 minutes. Serves 2 to 4.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Put into crock-pot with bacon crumbled on top and cook on high for 1 hour.

title: aunt em's salad dressing
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: knock you nakeds
directions: Combine cake mix, nuts, 1/3 cup milk and butter and mix well. Press half the mixture into the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: mushroom-cheese appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Press dough in bottom of pan.
Brown sausage and drain.
Mix sausage, mayo and onions.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems of mushrooms and mix into sausage mixture.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Place mushrooms in rows on dough.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover loosely with aluminum foil and bake 20 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Remove foil.
After removing foil, bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes and cut into 35 bite-sized pieces.

title: apple macaroon pie
directions: Line
pie
pan
with pastry.
Place apples in pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Sprinkle over apples. Dot with 1 tablespoon
butter.
Bake
at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar,
tablespoon
butter,
egg, milk and coconut. Sprinkle over hot pie.
Bake 30 minutes more.

title: fruit torte
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add egg and fruit cocktail. Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch pan (spray pan with Pam).

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Halve slices.
Melt butter in 9-inch round pan, 1 1/2-inches high.
Stir in brown sugar and 1 tablespoon reserved pineapple liquid.
Add water to remaining liquid to make 2/3 cup.
Arrange pineapple and cherries in pan.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Grease sides and bottom of 9-inch pie plate. Press hash browns into pie plate to form crust.
Brush with melted butter and bake for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle ham, onions, mushrooms and cheeses over crust.
Beat cream, eggs and salt and pour over cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.
I brown crust, add ingredients and then freeze before baking.

title: cracker snack
directions: In medium paper bag or plastic bag, mix all ingredients (except oil) and shake well.
Pour oil into bag and shake well again.
Store in tightly covered container.
Make at least 10 hours before serving.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine chicken, onion, oil, juice, peppers, garlic and salsa in a sealed plastic bag.
Marinate 2 to 24 hours in refrigerator. Grill or broil chicken and vegetables 5-inches from heat for 5 to 8 minutes per side,
while bringing marinade to a boil.
Cut chicken and vegetables into thin strips.
Divide among tortillas and drizzle with marinade.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up.
Serve with salsa, guacamole, sour cream, etc.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything (except pecans) thoroughly, then stir in pecans.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or 325° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Add combined dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Add sliced apples; mix well. Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: spicy hamburger relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions, green peppers, red peppers and salt. Let stand overnight.
The next morning, rinse thoroughly and mix well with brown sugar, cornstarch, turmeric, vinegar, dry mustard, nutmeg, coarse pepper and red peppers.
Mix well and boil for 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt; beat well and set aside.
In a 10-inch iron skillet, melt brown sugar and butter, stirring constantly.
Arrange pineapple slices in the brown sugar mixture, putting a cherry in the center of each slice and between slices. Pour cake batter carefully over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn out onto cake plate.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Put in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Ice with French Icing.

title: company pot roast
directions: Brown roast and onion in hot oil.
Add all ingredients, except vegetables.
Simmer, covered, for 2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes and cook until they are tender.
Discard cinnamon sticks. To thicken gravy, add 2 tablespoons of cornstarch to hot water and stir in.

title: carmelitas(tastes like a candy bar)
directions: In top of double boiler, melt caramels and evaporated milk. Stir until smooth.
Slice cookie dough 1/4-inch thick.
Pat dough to make a crust in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over warm cookie base.
Carefully spread caramel mixture on top.
Cool 1 to 2 hours.
Cut into 36 squares.
Top each with pecan half.

title: danish stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix ground veal and pork with other ingredients.
Roll stuffing in blanched cabbage leaves.
Cook in salted water until tender, about 25 minutes.
Brown cracker crumbs in butter and sprinkle over top of cabbage rolls after they have been placed on the platter for serving.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: *If nuts are omitted, use 1 1/2 cups semi-sweet chocolate chips.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers in large bowl and add candied fruit and pecans. Melt over low heat the marshmallows in condensed milk and pour over crackers, fruit and pecans in bowl.
Butter lightly your hands and work this mixture thoroughly.
Put into a loaf pan that has been lined with wax paper and sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: world's easiest peanut butter fudge
directions: All you have to do with this delicious recipe is simply heat the icing in the microwave for about 1 minute (or until completely melted).
Stir together with entire jar of peanut butter and quickly spread into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Let fudge harden in refrigerator or on the counter; cut and serve.
Quick and scrumptious.

title: barbecued salmon
directions: Place bacon in bottom of a baking dish.
Sprinkle salmon with salt and pepper; lay on top of bacon.
Saute garlic, onion and green peppers together for 3 minutes in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over salmon.
Bake in a 400° preheated oven for 30 minutes, basting often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans and beef
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add all other ingredients. Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date chews
directions: Cream
margarine and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla
and
flour;
mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: main dish chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken until done.
Cut into bite size pieces. Spray 2-quart casserole dish with vegetable oil spray.
Layer (arrange) chicken, then broccoli, soup, then cheese. Prepare stuffing as directed on package. Spoon stuffing on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham delight
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: amish sweet bread
directions: Days 1 2, 3 and 4:
Stir starter.

title: spinach and cream cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 can of onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° until heated.

title: j. b. barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all and cook until hot.
Put on boiled meats when meat is tender.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Stir pudding and dry cake mix together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels and nuts onto cake batter.
Place in a 350° oven and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, bell peppers and garlic in one stick of butter. Add parsley flakes, onion tops, soup, shrimp, rice, bread pieces, and hot water. Add salt and pepper, if desired. Cook 8 to 10 minutes. Pour in a 2 qt. casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs and butter pats. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Delicious!

title: ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients to make sauce.
Put half of the sauce over ribs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn ribs and pour on remaining sauce.
Bake at 300° for another hour.

title: no fry donuts
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, shortening and 2 cups flour. Beat 1/2 minute
on low speed.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for about 30 seconds.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients into a 1-gallon ice cream freezer. Stir well.
Fill to the line with milk.
Freeze until hard.
May be soft frozen for milk shakes.

title: fruit soup(swedish christmas pudding)
directions: Combine milk, corn meal, tapioca, ginger and salt.
Heat until thickened and it just starts to boil.
Stir constantly to mix in the corn meal.
Remove from the heat and add the molasses.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart deep baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until well set.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: grilled snapper
directions: Mix lemon juice, garlic, salt and oil.
Pat onto snapper; grill until flakes.
(It does not take long.)

title: california salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given and spread Miracle Whip, mixed with sugar, over top.
Refrigerate overnight or 6 hours. Toss before serving and add grated Cheddar cheese.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in water with oil and salt.
Cook meat in oil until brown.
Drain.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup tomato juice until smooth.
Stir into meat with other tomatoes, juices, onion and seasonings.
Layer in baking dish:
meat, noodles, cheese; repeat. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or a little longer, if necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine soup, chicken, veggies, cooked rice and water. Mix well and spread in a baking dish. Top with crackers. Bake 20 minutes.

title: garden scramble(makes 6 servings)
directions: In small bowl, beat together eggs, milk, black pepper and marjoram; set aside.
In skillet, over medium heat, cook celery, red pepper, green pepper and chives in margarine until tender; add egg mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally until set.
Serve immediately.

title: corn chowder no. 1
directions: Use a large pot.
Saute carrots and onions in butter until they are just tender.
Add everything else and heat.
May be frozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy, add sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix. Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas; mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in a greased bread pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: swiss steak
directions: Wipe meat with clean damp cloth.
Cut in 2-inch square pieces. Mix flour, salt and pepper together and pound into meat.
Brown onion and meat in Crisco.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and water. Cover and cook slowly 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sky high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in mashed berries and water; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour into a large bowl.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally, until mixture is slightly warm.
Fold in remaining berries.
Pile into shell.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Whip the cream until soft peaks form.
Sprinkle pudding mix over cream and whip until stiff. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chips and butter; stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half of the mixture firmly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla. Mix well and pour into pan. Top with crumb mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool completely and chill thoroughly. Cut into bars and store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Skin chicken pieces; place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Add can of water before covering chicken. Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Layer first four ingredients in dish.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Sprinkle top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Transfer to a greased angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: chocolate espresso cheesecake
directions: In large bowl, soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Blend cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter in a medium size bowl. Lightly butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Press crust firmly over the bottom and halfway up the sides of pan.
Chill briefly before adding the filling.
Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Dissolve Espresso in the 2 tablespoons of hot water.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Combine.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Lay uncooked chicken pieces on top of soup mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Seal over top with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Do not uncover before baking.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: mary's vidalia onion dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with sliced Baguette bread.

title: classic beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef, half at a time, in oil.

Drain. Return meat to pan and add onion, tomatoes or juice, water, bouillon, tapioca, garlic, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil, then bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Stir in vegetables.
Cover; continue baking for 1 hour, until tender.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Rinse mushrooms.
Cover with 1 cup boiling water in small bowl.
Reserve.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in large pot over medium-low heat until tender but not browned 5 minutes.
Increase heat.
Add beef; brown on all sides.
Add beef broth, water, carrots, celery, salt, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf.
Drain mushrooms, adding liquid to pot.
Crush mushrooms.
Add to soup. Bring to boiling.
Lower heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add turnips, zucchini and barley.
Return to simmer.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more or until barley is tender.
Melt butter in small skillet over medium-low heat; stir in flour until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly
until flour turns light brown color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in about 1 cup soup liquid until smooth.
Stir flour mixture back into soup until smooth.
Remove bay leaf.
Add parsley.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: mac and stuff
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Meanwhile, bring water, peas, hot dogs and margarine to boil in a large saucepan. Stir in stuffing mix and cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir stuffing mixture into macaroni and cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: chili cornbread pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is browned; drain. Stir in undrained beans, tomato sauce, tomato paste and taco seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring often. Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate or shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Open the package of cornbread twists. Do not unroll dough. Using a knife, separated twists at the seams. Place separated twists between 2 sheets of wax paper and flatten with a rolling pin.

Press flattened dough in bottom and up sides of pie plate. Spoon beef mixture into crust. Combine the sour cream and flour. Spread over meat mixture to within 1/2-inch of the edges. Sprinkle cheese and corn chips over top.
Place pie plate on baking sheet. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Allow pie to stand 10 minutes before serving. Top with green onion, tomato or other garnishes as desired.
Makes 8 main dish servings.

title: bobbie's soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat slowly, simmer, stirring often. Burns easily.

title: winter day soup
directions: Cook until cabbage, potatoes and onions are done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Put half in skillet.
Add ground beef and onion, then add cheese and chopped jalapeno peppers.
Cover with remaining cornmeal mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: In 3 separate containers, cover the ground pears, chopped onions and peppers with boiling water.
Let set for 1 hour. Drain these completely.
Combine all ingredients in a large container.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.
Process in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 pints.
Delicious with meats and vegetables.
Great on hot dogs.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion thin.
Rub bowl with cut cloves of garlic.
Mix cucumbers and onions in bowl.
Mix sour cream and other ingredients well; mix with cucumbers and onions.
Chill for several hours.
This gets better with time.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in airtight container.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Crumble bread and soak in milk.
Mix with other ingredients except tomato juice.
Shape into balls.
Put in casserole.
Pour tomato juice over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Brown chopped onion and celery in oil.
Add flour and blend well.
Add broth and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire, seasoning and chicken.
Heat and serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix all four ingredients.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cover with sour cream.

title: yummy fruit dip
directions: Mix with an electric mixer until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: taco sauce for chips
directions: Melt all together on medium heat. Serve in warmer.

title: peach cobbler (using biscuit mix)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix cornstarch and cinnamon in saucepan. Stir in a little of peaches liquid until smooth.
Stir in remaining liquid and peaches. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened, about 4 minutes.

Place into 1-quart casserole dish. Stir mix and sugar together. Stir in water until dry ingredients are barely moistened. Spread on top of peach mixture. Bake until top is lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: pink peanut patties
directions: Cook everything except the vanilla to a firm ball stage or 250° on a candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy and thick.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Beat with wooden spoon.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for about 5 minutes until soft-ball stage. Add the peanut butter, vanilla and Marshmallow Fluff. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 or smaller pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 4 minutes; drain and put in casserole.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together; pour over broccoli.
Cover with layer of cheese slices.
Melt 1 stick oleo; mix with the crushed crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 34 minutes.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Stir salt into dry bread crumbs.
Dip fish into milk; then coat with bread crumbs and place on a well-greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour melted margarine over fish.
Place pan so it is slightly above center of oven.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: hot apple punch
directions: Heat all ingredients together. Serve hot or cold.

title: norwegian tea cakes
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in vanilla.
Combine almonds, chocolate and the remaining sugar into the flour and fold into the egg whites.
Spoon into 12 small fluted paper baking cups set in muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a rack or serve warm. Makes 12 small cakes.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix together thoroughly and chill.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add small amount of hot mixture.
Stir and add to other raisin mixture and cook 5 minutes.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nuts and serve with whipped cream.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the California blend and drain (do not over cook).
Mix with cream of mushroom soup and cheese in casserole dish. Top with crackers, then add melted butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix in order given very thoroughly and refrigerate.
Always stir before serving.

title: sugar cookies(3 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Combine all ingredients.
Beat vigorously until well blended.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto prepared baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove cookies and sprinkle lightly with sugar.

title: microwave broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, combine soup mix, milk and if desired, nutmeg.
Stir in vegetables and cheese. Cover and cook on 100% power for 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir and sprinkle with crackers and if desired, paprika before serving.
Makes 4 servings, 106 calories.

title: meatball chowder
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, eggs, parsley, garlic salt and cracker crumbs with a little milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into walnut size balls and dip in flour.
Heat oil and lightly brown meat balls.
Add remaining ingredients (except corn) and boil. Cover and cook slowly until tender.
Add corn last.
This is even better the next day, reheated.

title: lasagne
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and onions; cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, salt, sugar, oregano, basil, red pepper and water.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: mathew's smoked dogs
directions: Cook until dogs are done.
Eat with smoked beans or regular or in a roll of your choice.

title: apple cake
directions: Can add raisins, too.

title: bermuda salad bowl
directions: Separate cauliflower in flowerets; slice thinly crosswise. Slice onion; separate in rings.
Marinate cauliflower, onion, olives, in French dressing for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, add cheese and lettuce broken in bite-sized pieces; toss lightly. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: In skillet, brown chicken parts.
