Pour off fat.
Stir in tomato soup, sour cream, onions and paprika.
Cover and simmer for approximately 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir and serve over noodles.

title: crunchy peanut butter puff parfaits
directions: Prepare the pudding according to package directions.
Stir in the peanut butter.
For each serving, spoon about 1/3 cup of pudding into the bottom of a tall glass.
Add 1/4 cup cereal.
Top with 6 banana slices.
Repeat with the rest of the pudding and cereal.
Top with banana slices.
Serve right away.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese puff on creamed chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse frozen peas under running cold water to separate; drain.
Place peas and chicken in 2-quart casserole or 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Heat soup, sour cream, salt and pepper just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in 1 tablespoon parsley and 1 tablespoon pimiento.
Stir 1 1/2 cups of soup mixture into peas and chicken.
Place in oven while preparing topping.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into sticks about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour, then dip into egg beaten with milk.
Roll in crumbs and fry in hot deep fat (380° on a frying thermometer) until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday gumdrop fruitcake
directions: Butter and flour two loaf pans or one tube pan.
Sift flour and soda.
Combine eggs, mincemeat, condensed milk, gumdrops and nuts. Fold together until well blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for two hours or until center springs back when done.

title: apple cinnamon coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream and butter on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour half into a greased 8 inch square baking dish or pan.
Top with apples. Combine the sugar, nuts and cinnamon, sprinkle half over the apples.
Top with remaining batter and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Make Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and beat with mixer until smooth.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Mix well.
Add the marshmallows by hand.
Place in a square dish and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: jo jo's ham delights
directions: Slice rolls completely through the middle.
Cream margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Spread tops and bottoms with creamed mixture.
Then add boiled ham and Swiss cheese, divided evenly over rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut into individual rolls.
They may be frozen for later use.
Yields 60 rolls.

title: bacon-wrapped chicken breast
directions: Top chicken with cheese and ham.
Wrap with bacon.
Place in uncovered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until bacon is brown.

title: rice surprise
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and rice.
Put half of rice mixture in dish.
Sprinkle on chopped chilies, cover with Cheddar cheese and add remaining rice.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil and grease with 1 teaspoon butter and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine powdered sugar, cocoa and salt.
Melt remaining butter and milk and vanilla.
Stir into sugar, mix until blended.
Whisk until smooth.
Stir in M&M's and pour into pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Lift out of pan and discard foil.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until golden brown.
Add broccoli right from the package, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer for a few minutes until broccoli is thawed; add rice.
Simmer a few minutes more. Bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Melt the butter in a 3-quart saucepan; add brown sugar and salt.
Stir until combined.
Stir in corn syrup and mix well. Gradually add the condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Insert candy thermometer and cook over medium heat until candy reaches 245° (firm ball stage).
This will take around 12 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Mix well and then pour into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yield: 2 1/2 pounds.

title: lettuce layer salad
directions: Layer all items in order listed.
Fits well in 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: vegetable relish(chow-chow pickle)
directions: Combine all vegetables in bowl and cover with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Thoroughly rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over vegetables.
Bring to boil, boil gently for 5 minutes.
Ladle into jars.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes 9 pints.

title: apple ambrosia
directions: Put apples in greased 8-inch square dish.
Pour orange juice over top.
Blend butter and brown sugar well; add remaining ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Spread evenly over apples. Place dish in center of microwave oven.
Cook at High power 8 to 10 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold, with ice cream if desired.
Can be baked in conventional oven at 400° until apples are tender, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: herb vinegar
directions: Into glass jar place chili pepper, garlic and oregano.
Heat cider vinegar until hot, but do not boil.
Pour into jar with herbs.
Let vinegar cool, then cover and store in cool dark place for up to 1 year.

title: never fail fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit and nuts in a large mixing bowl.
Add coconut and mix well with hands.
Add flour; mix.
Add milk and mix well.
Pack firmly in a 10-inch lightly greased loose bottom tube pan (line bottom with greased wax paper).
If desired, decorate top with pecan halves and cherries.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove and run knife around edge and remove rim of pan.
When barely warm, remove tube bottom and wax paper.
Keeps indefinitely or freeze.

title: crockpot macaroni and cheese pie
directions: Grease crockpot or spray with pam. Mix all ingredients, saving 1 cup of cheese to sprinkle on top. Cook covered on low for 3 hours. Recipe can be doubled.

title: white castle burgers
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; press onto cookie sheets with edges to thinly cover whole sheet.
Prick with fork.
Bake about 10 minutes at 400°.
Cut into square and put on party rolls with a pickle slice on each.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and stem mushrooms.
Chop stems and place in frying pan with butter.
Add onion, salt and pepper and saute.
Add sherry and whipping cream and stir until mixture is thick.

title: creamy pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until white.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan for one hour and 45 minutes at 325°.
This cake freezes well.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cool.
Mix the next 3 ingredients; beat well.
Spread on cake.

title: toasted tuna buns
directions: Combine tuna fish, onion, chopped pickle and mayonnaise. Split 6 round buns and spread with tuna fish mixture.
Top with 2 slices of cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: lemon eagle brand pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fold until well blended.
Fill 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Let chill approximately 1 hour.

title: rice salad(san francisco jr. league; yield: 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Place all in serving bowl.

title: herb blend for pork
directions: Crush dried herbs and blend thoroughly.

title: hearty hamburger stew
directions: Spray a Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray. Brown meat and onion.

Drain fat. Add water, tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, carrots, bay leaf and pepper. Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Add beans, corn and pasta. Return to boil. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: In frying pan, brown chicken in a little olive oil and place in shallow baking dish.
Saute peppers, mushrooms (sliced) and garlic in same skillet just until limp.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake, lightly covered, for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with pasta and good bread for cleaning your plate.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seed in pan at 350°.
Mix together shredded cabbage, bean sprouts, sliced mushrooms and chopped green onions in bowl.
Combine almonds, sesame seed, sunflower seeds, crushed Ramen noodles and chow mein noodles in bowl.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream and oil. Fold in corn, onion and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Grease	13
x
8-inch
baking
dish.
Pour pineapple in dish. Add
blueberries.
Sprinkle
sugar
over	this.
Then sprinkle cake
mix
over.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Add nuts. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. About
halfway
through
baking time cut down center with knife and let some of the juice run out.	This allows it to cook all through.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Cook celery in small amount of chicken broth.
In a large container, combine all ingredients, except the chicken broth.
Add enough broth to make it a juicy mixture.
Bake in a greased baking pan or bowl in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: mom's gingerbread
directions: Add together first 3 ingredients and stir.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Use greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until done.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Place all ingredients in order (except sausage) into blender container.
Blend on high speed until smooth, about 1 minute. Transfer mixture to 1 1/2-quart saucepan; cook and stir constantly over medium-high heat until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add sausage and 3 tablespoons sausage drippings.

title: ham 'n cheese croissants
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend margarine, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion in a medium bowl.
Split croissants and spread margarine mixture on bottom half of each croissant. Place a slice of ham and a slice of cheese on top of this.
Bake on cookie sheet for 5 minutes and remove from oven.
Spread margarine mixture on top half of each croissant and place top on sandwich. Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar, salt and eggs together.
Add pinto beans.
Mix well.
Let ingredients stand for 1/2 hour.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° until crust begins to brown.
Reduce temperature to 375° and bake 30 minutes longer until center of pie is set.
May top with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Serve warm.

title: chili with beans
directions: Chop onion.
Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain. Add tomato soup and stir to mix.
Mix chili powder and flour with enough water to make a smooth paste.
Stir flour mixture into ground beef mixture.
Add crushed tomatoes, stirring to mix well. Add beans, stirring to mix well.
Cook over medium heat for about 30 minutes or until bubbly, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.

title: blue cheese salad dressing(from the 1920's, before anyone ever heard of sour cream.)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl, add liquids and stir.
This was in 1920.
Today, put everything into food processor and give it a whirl.
Add blue cheese, as much as you like.
Try not to whirl too much because the dressing looks nicest with flecks of cheese showing.
Add garlic cloves and medium sized onion to dressing. These can be removed in a few days.
Chopped watercress is nice to add.

title: southwest vegetable soup
directions: Bring tomato soup, chicken broth, water, corn, green beans, tomatoes, chilies, taco seasoning and chicken to a boil over medium heat.
Add tortillas and cheese; stir until melted and tortillas are soft.
Serve with corn tortillas or cornbread.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Mix all together; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: danny's favorite valentine truffles
directions: Heat cream in medium saucepan until small bubbles form around edge.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate and butter; stir until smooth.
If desired, add flavorings or toasted nuts or leave as is. Chill until firm.
Scoop chocolate and form 1-inch balls.
(Talk about "finger-licking good" once you are finished.)
Coat in cocoa or sugar.
Refrigerate on a clean cookie sheet or tin.

title: coated pecans
directions: In microwave oven, melt oleo 1 minute on High in 2-quart covered casserole.
Add and cook 2 minutes on High, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in pecans; cook 3 to 5 minutes on High. Remove from microwave and stir.
Spread on waxed paper.
Enjoy.

title: almond buffet casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and soup to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover, reduce heat and very gently boil 25 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
Remove from heat.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots, 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix vinegar, sugar, oil and tomato soup; heat to boiling.
Add onion and green pepper; boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Will keep about 1 week in refrigerator.

title: aunt susan's brown candy
directions: Pour 1 pint sugar in a heavy skillet and place over a low flame.
Begin stirring with a long handle spoon and keep sugar moving so it will not scorch.
Pour remaining 2 pints of sugar together with 1 pint of milk into a deep heavy skillet and set over a low fire to cook slowly while melting sugar in skillet.
As soon as all sugar is melted begin pouring it into the skillet slowly and stirring constantly.
Pour a very fine stream from skillet and continue cooking and stirring until mixture forms a firm ball when dropped into glass of cold water.
After test is made, turn out fire and lightly add soda, stirring vigorously as it foams up high and you stir.
Let it cool on table about 20 minutes at room temperature.
Add vanilla and nuts, then beat until a dull appearance and turn into a buttered plate or square dish; cut while warm into squares.

title: real mayonnaise
directions: Diced apple, seedless grapes, diced celery and chopped nuts with Cool Whip and dressing.

title: main dish with vegetables
directions: In large baking dish, place stew beef, cut in small pieces. Add tomatoes and mixed vegetables.
Sprinkle gravy mix.
Put salt and pepper on top.
Pour water and catsup on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix ingredients
and roll into balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Put canned soups and milk into crock-pot.
Fry bacon until well done, then cool. Crumble into small pieces and add to crock-pot.
Saute onion and celery in bacon grease, then add to crock-pot.
Add diced potatoes to crock-pot.
Cook on medium for 2 hours.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in rapidly boiling water.
Quickly dissolve the sauce and mix in the applesauce.
Pour into oiled 5 cup mold or casserole dish.
Chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat pies
directions: Mix thoroughly meat, onion and salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle lemon juice over meat and let stand while rolling out dough.
(Follow instructions on box for pizza.)
Roll out and cut with a glass (size of biscuits), then roll biscuits real thin. Fill center with meat mixture (size of a walnut), then pinch 3 corners, leaving center open.
Bake in hot oven until dough is golden brown.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Return to pan and mix with all ingredients listed.
Put into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° until sauce bubbles and crumbs are brown (about 25 to 30 minutes).

title: plain pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Beat eggs; stir in milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons onto hot ungreased griddle.
Bake until underside is golden brown and bubbles appear over surface. Turn and bake other side.
Serve with butter, syrup or a cinnamon and sugar mix, if desired.
Makes 20 pancakes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear bread into small pieces into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. In medium bowl, beat eggs; add milk and spices.
Stir and pour over bread.
Sprinkle sausage over top.
Cover with grated or chopped cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can make night before, refrigerate and bake in the morning.

title: spicy vegetables
directions: Chop vegetables in bite-size pieces.
Place oil, cumin seed and onion in frypan.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over medium heat in covered pan until fork-tender (approximately 20 minutes).
May need to add some water if needed occasionally.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole (2 1/2-quart).
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Brown in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow bowl.
Dip each chicken breast in beaten egg, then roll in bread crumb mixture to evenly coat.
Place chicken on a cookie sheet or jelly roll pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over; bake 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: firehouse baked beans
directions: Crumble and brown either sausage (Italian) or hamburger. Meat preference depends on how spicy a taste you want. After browning, set aside.
Saut the garlic, onion and pepper until tender. Combine meat, sauteed mixture and beans in a baking dish or bean pot. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Yield: 10 servings.

title: yummy canapes
directions: Mix ingredients, cream cheese, sour cream, onion, green pepper and chopped beef.
Put in pie plate.
Heat in medium oven.
Add nuts which have been toasted in butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Serve with crackers.

title: norma's layer dip
directions: Mix avocados, juice, mayonnaise, onions and seasonings. Spread in Pyrex dish, 8 x 8-inches.
Layer salsa, then sour cream, then cheese.
If desired, top with fresh cubed tomatoes and black olives.
Open bag of tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: choco-dot cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, shortening, margarine, vanilla and eggs in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in candies and nuts.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press 3 or 4 additional candies in each cookie, if desired.
Bake until light brown, 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter. Mix all ingredients together (minus Jiffy mix). Add Jiffy mix; stir. Bake 45+ minutes at 350°.
Center should be firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil until fluffy.
Add flour, vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir in zucchini and other fruits if you are using any of them.
Fill loaf pans 1/2 full.
Makes 2 or 3 pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken, potatoes and onion until done; then add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: baked garlic, tomato and zucchini casserole
directions: Coat a large shallow casserole dish with a thin layer of olive oil.
Layer the zucchini slices alternately with the tomato slices, overlapping slightly.
Sprinkle the garlic slices and shredded basil on top and season to taste.
Finish with a thin layer of grated cheese.
Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Bake the casserole for about 30 minutes until the vegetables are tender.
Serves 20 as part of a buffet.
Can be made a day ahead without sprinkling the cheese on it-covered and refrigerated.
Top with cheese and bake when ready to serve.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple; add all other ingredients.
Place in mold pan.
Chill.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cream together Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese.
In another bowl, mix milk, instant pudding mix and vanilla.
Add to Eagle Brand milk and cheese.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 box Cool Whip. Alternate layers of bananas and vanilla wafers.
Layer remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: schnitzel beans
directions: Dice bacon or ham and fry crisp.
Add onion and brown.
Add beans and brown slightly.
Add tomatoes and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until beans are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add apples.
Mix well and add pecans.
Bake in moderate oven about 350° until done.
This makes a large cake.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, white corn syrup, water and salt to boil.
Add peanuts and coloring.
Cook until reaches hard ball stage.
Remove from fire.
Add butter or margarine and beat until smooth.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut in squares.
May also be dropped from tablespoon onto waxed paper for varying shapes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk in a bowl. Fold in pie filling, pineapple, sour cream, whipped topping and pecans, blending well. Cover and chill well before serving. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bring margarine and water to a boil; add flour all at once, stirring rapidly.
Cook until thick and leaves the sides of the pan.
Remove from heat and beat in the eggs, one at a time. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes, then at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Stir-fry hamburger until brown; drain.
Add water and catsup; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add rice and cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add cheese and stir lightly.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: pudding dip(for fruit)
directions: Make pudding with milk; let set.
Beat pudding into sour cream.
Refrigerate.

title: black and gold marble cake
directions: Melt chocolate and add hot water and sugar and stir until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir shortening enough to soften and sift in dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and vanilla and mix all until flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Pour half of the batter into a second bowl.
Add chocolate mixture and blend well.
Alternate plain and chocolate mixtures and pour all into baking pan.
With a knife cut through batter once in a wide, zigzag course to marble.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in a greased and floured oblong pan.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large bowl. beat eggs and milk. Add bread; mix gently an let stand for 5 minutes. Add beef, onion, baking powder, salt and pepper; mix well (mixture will be soft). Shape into 1 inch balls. In a large skillet brown meatballs, a few at a time, in shortening. Place in an ungreased 3 quart baking dish. In a bowl, stir soups and milk until smooth; pour over meatballs. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; beat egg.
Add buttermilk and onion.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonful into hot grease.
When done, they will float.
Drain on paper towels.

title: spoonbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and sugar together.
Scald with boiling water.
Add melted butter.
Beat eggs and add milk to eggs.
Put the two mixtures together.
Add baking powder.
Put into baking pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: coconut cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture alternately with cream of coconut, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in the lemon rind and vanilla.

title: onions in foil
directions: With sharp knife, cut out onion centers and chop.
Toss chopped onions with rest of ingredients.
Fill each onion cavity with about 2 tablespoons stuffing.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make paste from margarine, flour and milk.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Add salt and pepper; remove from heat.
Coat pan. Spread sauce, a layer of potatoes, onions, sauce and cheese. Repeat layers and cover.
Bake at 375° for 2 to 3 hours or until potatoes are done.
Remove cover and sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Soften cheese.
Add all ingredients except tortillas and mix well.
Spread on tortillas and roll up.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice about 3/4-inch thick and place on tray.
Good served with picante sauce.
Serves 20.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for water.
Just before placing in pan, add water.
Mixture will be very thin, but when baked it will be light and spongy.
Square cake pan is best.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Top with confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter should be lumpy.
Spoon batter into 12 (2 1/2-inch) greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring when lightly touched.
Serve warm.

title: heath candy bar cake(skor candy may be used)
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When done, poke holes in cake with wooden spoon handle about 1-inch apart.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, then add oats, cereal, nuts and coconut.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Drop by teaspoonfuls or roll in balls.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked fish
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.
Combine bouillon, wine vinegar, celery flakes and ginger.
Pour over fish in pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well
crushed
pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoon sugar. Bake
at 350° for 10 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Mix
cream
cheese and 1 cup sugar; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add
frozen berries; break up with fork while stirring. Chill
until
slightly
thickened.	Pour
over Cool Whip layer. Chill until set.

title: one step pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients in pie pan.
Shape with hands, pressing in pan.
Prick and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or bake with filling.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into crust in buttered pie plate (10-inch).
In skillet, cook ground beef or sausage, onion, and green pepper until vegetables are tender and meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, salt, and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Fill pie with tomato mixture.
Cover with foil and chill in refrigerator for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Pour part of the oil in pan.
Heat in oven.
Mix remaining oil and rest of ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
margarine.
Add Wesson oil.	Add egg yolks one
at
a	time.
Add
Seven-Up
and flour alternately. Beat egg whites
and
fold into other mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake
at 325° in a greased and floured Bundt pan or deep iron skillet for a more crusty finish.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook first five ingredients about 20 minutes. Add broccoli and cauliflower. Cook until tender. Add sliced or cubed cheese and soup. Let cheese melt, stirring occasionally. Serves 4 easily. Can also add zucchini or green beans.

title: ham and peas fettucine
directions: Cook fettucine as directed.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter; stir in garlic powder.
Gradually add whipping cream, Parmesan cheese and sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated.
Combine fettucine, green peas, sauce and ham.
Stir gently to coat.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add buttered bread crumbs as topping.
Bake in hot oven until topping is crusty.

title: crockery cooking
directions: Brown beef on all sides in oil in skillet. Place in slow cooker. Layer onions, potatoes, carrots and lima beans over beef. Mix tomatoes and seasonings together in bowl. Pour over meat and vegetables. Cover. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl; make well in center. In separate bowl, mix yolks, salt and sugar.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Add corn; mix.
Whip whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Cook until golden brown.

title: bea's corn salad
directions: Chop ingredients and mix everything together.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish. Mix rice, soup mix, water and the cream of chicken soup together. Spread in baking dish. Salt and pepper chicken breast and place over rice mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and brown on broil until a golden brown.

title: apple filled oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Combine apples, raisins, pecans, granulated sugar and water. Cook and stir until thick and apples are tender (about 10 minutes). Cream the butter and brown sugar. Beat in eggs. Sift dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir in oatmeal. Set aside 3/4 cup dough. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Make small depression and put in apple filling.
Top with small amount of dough.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Turn oven to 450°.
In a small bowl, stir sugar and cinnamon until mixed.
Cut biscuits in half.
Dip tops in melted margarine, then in the cinnamon sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet with the tops up.
Bake for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: he man cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
In a large bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Add the two mixtures together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: new york crumb cake
directions: Place rack in center of oven and heat to 325°. Lightly brush a 9 x 12-inch baking pan with vegetable oil, dust with flour and tap to remove excess; set aside. In a medium bowl, sift together 1 1/2 cups flour, granulated sugar, baking power, and salt; set aside. In a second bowl, whisk together egg, milk, vegetable oil and vanilla. Using a rubber spatula, fold dry ingredients into egg mixture. Spread batter evenly into prepared pan and set aside. In a medium bowl, combine remaining 2 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour melted butter over flour mixture and toss with a rubber spatula until large crumbs form. Sprinkle crumbs over batter and bake, rotating pan after 10 minutes. Continue baking until a cake tester comes out clean, about 10 minutes more. Transfer baking pan to a wire rack to cool. Dust with confectioners' sugar. Using a serrated knife, cut into 3-inch squares. Store in an airtight container for up to 3 days.

title: potato chowder
directions: Melt butter in a
quart
Dutch
oven.
Saute
onion, celery and carrots until
tender,	about 8 minutes.
Add potatoes, water and
bouillon
granules and simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine flour with 1/2 cup cream to form
a
smooth paste.
Stir in vegetable mixture and add remaining cream
and
seasonings.
Bring
to boil over medium heat, stirring
constantly.
Boil
and stir one minute. Reduce heat to low.
Stir	in
cheese
until
melted.
Do	not boil. Serve with assorted cheeses and crackers.

title: orange alaskan chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Make a well; add in order the oil, 5 egg yolks, water and orange peel.
Stir until smooth.
Measure egg whites and add cream of tartar into a large bowl.
Beat until whites form stiff peaks.
Gradually pour the egg yolk mixture over beaten whites; gently fold until just blended.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake about 75 minutes or until top springs back when touched.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Pound steak until thin, rub in salt, pepper, and paprika. Spread with mushrooms; arrange in layer. Blanket with layer of thin sliced onions, add pimentoes and cover with rolled bread crumbs.
With beater, combine butter, boiling water, and add raw egg. Dribble thin mixture over bread crumbs, arrange stuffed olives in a row on the long side of steak.
Begin the roll of meat around the olives. Tie roll with strong cord. Flour the outside and brown. Add 1-2 cups cooking wine and roast at 350° for at least 2 hrs.

title: good salad
directions: Shred lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Lay cauliflower on top of lettuce in bowl.
Cover with the mayo.
Break onion in rings and layer on mayo.
Sprinkle on bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight. Toss when ready to serve.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well and pour into cookie sheet, 10 x 15. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: snickers-bar cookies
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/2-inch slices, then cut each slice in half.
Take a piece of dough and flatten in your hand.
Wrap 1 candy bar in each piece of dough.
Work it until none of the candy is showing.
Use a pinch more of dough if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all and shape into ball.
Roll in parsley or nuts.

title: cornmeal batter rolls
directions: Combine 3 1/2 cups of flour and the yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt, just until shortening is melted.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in cornmeal and remaining flour.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size.
Stir down.
Fill 24 muffin cups 2/3 full; let rise.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: quick cheese coffee cake
directions: Buy 1 box of baking mix.
Find pancake recipe on side panel. Follow directions.
Serve.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Chop vegetables very fine.
Cook or fry until tender, adding soy sauce, pepper, Accent and garlic salt to taste.
Let set overnight in covered container.
Drain and wrap in prepared wrappers.
Fry until brown.
Use an egg white or flour and water to close wrappers.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak biscuits and milk together overnight.
Stir in sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into a square pan and bake in a 400° oven until firm and lightly browned.

title: focaccia
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Blend thoroughly remaining ingredients.
Add yeast mixture to blended ingredients. Blend in well.
Pour into two greased 5 x 9-inch pans.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Bake at 300° to 325° for approximately 55 minutes.

title: double crumble bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, nuts, cocoa and baking powder.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread marshmallows over cake evenly and bake 2 minutes more.
Cool.
In saucepan (low heat) melt chips and peanut butter until smooth, stirring.
Stir in cereal and spread on top of cooled bars.
Chill and cut into bars. Refrigerate.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend together flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate this mixture and sour cream into first mixture.
Spoon half of batter into angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Grease and flour very well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, salt and water together to hard-ball (250°) stage. Add butter and peanuts (peanuts crushed and skins blown off). Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until golden brown (300°). Remove from fire. Add vanilla, then add soda. Stir quickly until soda is thoroughly mixed. Spread on buttered cookie sheet until cool. Break into pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cooked broccoli, cheese, onion, salt and Mrs. Dash. Grease casserole dish.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream pumpkin pie
directions: Cook together until bubbling.
Cool to warm temperature.
Stir in 1 quart vanilla or butter pecan ice cream.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Freeze.

title: waffle mix
directions: Mix egg and sugar well.
Add butter, then milk.
Last, add flour.
Mix well.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings and discard tip ends.
Stir together soy sauce, vinegar, sugars, ginger and garlic for marinade.
Put wings in heavy plastic bag and pour in marinade. Close bag and place in a bowl in case the bag leaks.
Marinate at least 2 hours, overnight is best.
To cook place in a 13 x 9-inch oblong pan and bake at 350° for over 1 hour.
Yield:
12 servings.
Carbohydrate 8 g, protein 17 g, fat 7 g, calories per serving 163.
One serving = 1/2 bread exchange, 2 meat exchanges.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute margarine, onion and broccoli together until tender.
Add mushroom soup, milk and Velveeta.
Stir until hot.

title: butter tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into pie crust lined cupcake tins. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: italian home fries
directions: In a heavy 10 inch skillet, fry the bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and then crumble the bacon.
Leave the bacon grease in the skillet.
Add the potatoes and onions and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until potatoes begin to brown slightly.
Add the tomatoes and cover.
Reduce heat to low and cook until potatoes are tender, stirring often to prevent sticking. This usually takes about 20 minutes.
Be sure that the potatoes are fork tender.
Remove from heat and sprinkle the crumbled bacon and cheese over the top of the potatoes.
Cover and the heat from the potatoes will melt the cheese.
Serve warm.

title: boiled salad dressing
directions: Put first 5 ingredients on the stove to boil.
Thicken with eggs and flour; add butter.

title: pumpkin shortbread
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Cut in butter.
Press lightly in pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: easy malasadas
directions: Cut dough into 1-inch balls or cubes. Drop into hot oil and fry until golden brown. Drain and cool. Shake in bag of granulated sugar. Get out of the way of the crowd.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream together remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening together with sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Mix well.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll balls into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Cool on flat surface.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from tops of mushrooms, chop enough to measure 1/2 cup.
Cook half of mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons margarine over medium heat for 5 minutes, drain.
Repeat with remaining mushrooms and margarine.
Combine cheeses, mixing until well blended.
Stir in chopped stems and onions, fill mushrooms.
Place on cookie sheet, broil until golden brown.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: rocky road nut cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and salt together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts and margarine.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Cream the margarine. Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add egg, milk, dry ingredients and vanilla. Mix well. Gently fold in blueberries. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle top of each with 2 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hamburger skillet supper
directions: Brown beef; skim off excess fat.
Season meat with salt and pepper.
Stir in beans, pizza sauce and onion; heat until boiling.

title: low-fat potato skins
directions: Wet several potatoes.
Pierce potatoes several times with a fork.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Cool.
Scoop some potatoes out.
Cut into fourths.
Mash down crosswise with fork.
Drizzle skim milk on each one.
Squeeze low-fat margarine on each potato.
Salt and pepper.
Add low-fat or nonfat cheese.
Place under broiler for 2 to 4 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make small meatballs and bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Combine sauces and meat and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown chopped bacon and onion.
Pour off grease.
Drain juice from green beans.
Add bacon, onion and soup.
Mix good.
Pour into greased Pyrex.
Put onion rings on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, making 3 layers.
When completely cool, combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Blend well and chill.
Reserve 1 cup of sour cream.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs, oranges and juice.
Mix well. Divide into 2 greased layer pans.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pineapple and dry pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cakes.
Chill 1 hour before serving. Keep chilled.

title: soft shelled crab sandwich
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Put soft shelled crab in and sprinkle a little Old Bay and pepper.
Cover and cook slow for 5 minutes. Remove cover and increase heat.
Brown on both sides.
Serve on bread with mayonnaise or butter, lettuce and thin slice of tomato.
You may also like a thin slice of sweet onion on the sandwich.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend on high for 30 seconds.

title: almond oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add flavorings and eggs.
Mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add oats, cereal, nuts and raisins and mix well.

title: mark's polish sausage casserole
directions: Barely cover thick sliced sausage with water.
Add diced, raw potatoes and sauerkraut.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low. Simmer about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: tasty shrimp dip(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Mash or finely chop shrimp; mix all ingredients together.

title: arizona sunrise
directions: One-fifth is the base of pink lemonade (if this cannot be found, regular lemonade with food coloring may be used)

title: easy banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Stir in oil. Mash bananas, beat eggs and stir together. Combine both mixtures. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 250° for 1-1/2 to 2 hours.

title: apple butter
directions: Core and quarter unpeeled apples in 4 to 6-quart kettle or Dutch oven.
Combine apples and cider.
Cook until soft, about 30 minutes.
Press through food mill.
(Drain off excess apple cider if you don't want your butter to be thin.)
Boil gently for 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add sugar and spices; cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil gently, stirring frequently, until of desired thickness.
Carefully ladle the hot butter into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath (half pints) for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 half pints.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: goodey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, pecans, oleo and 1 egg with spoon.
Pat in a 16 x 11-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs with mixer.
Spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and combine all ingredients in a large cooker.
Simmer for 4 hours.
Freezes good.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine celery, chicken, mayonnaise, almonds, cheese, lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with chips.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.

title: grandma's whole turkey soup
directions: In a large pot, boil turkey wings until almost done, then add onions, sweet potato, parsnips, turnips and carrots.
Boil 30 minutes more, then add celery and parsley.
Cook until real tender and falling apart, then add matzo balls.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until matzo balls are warm thoroughly.
Makes 24 (1-cup) servings.

title: party meat balls
directions: Roll hamburger into little small balls, seasoned.
Then roll lightly over chopped onions.
Brown meat in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add chili sauce and grape jelly.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased pan lined with zwieback crumbs at bottom.
Add a little melted butter and cinnamon to the crumbs if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Whip sour cream with 1/4 to 1/2 cup of sugar and pour over cake.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Put in refrigerator and chill for at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 8 or more.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine cut up canned tomatoes, tomato sauce and all seasonings.
Brown chicken in 1/4 cup oil.
Remove chicken; cook onions and garlic until tender.
Return chicken to pan; add sauce and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add wine; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: muffins for a crowd
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Sift the flour again with the soda, cinnamon and salt; stir in the raisin bran and sugar.
Add the eggs, buttermilk and oil to the dry ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Line muffin tins with liners or grease well.
Fill 2/3 full and bake at 400°
for 20 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.
Keeps well in refrigerator and freezes well either before baking or baked.

title: beer batter
directions: Sift flour and starch together.
Beat egg yolk into beer.
Mix into flour.
Let stand one hour.
Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks.
Fold into batter.
Dip fish in batter and deep fry at 375°.

title: old-fashion doughnuts
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and sugar.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture, mixing well, then beat until batter is smooth.
Drop by teaspoon into 1 1/2 inches hot (375°) oil in deep saucepan.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes, until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening brown and white sugar.
Add 2 eggs.
Beat. Add all dry ingredients.
Make into small balls.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add salt.
Add sweet relish.
Add onion, eggs and celery salt.
Mix with mayonnaise.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to box directions.
Meanwhile, brown ground chuck in skillet until dry (or drain excess grease). Salt and pepper to taste.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat and let simmer.
Stir in approximately 1/2 of the cottage cheese and let melt slightly.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: apple delight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat at medium speed the eggs, sugar, and oil for two minutes.
Add sifted dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir in apple slices and walnuts. Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Trim
excess
fat
from
pork
chops.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and ginger.
Coat chops and brown well in oil in large skillet. Move
chops;
add
onion
and garlic and saute until tender. Combine
water, chili sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and soy sauce. Pour over chops, cover and simmer about 45 minutes until tender.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes. Beat in sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice. Add flour, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Fold in until well blended. Spread mixture in well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, grapes and walnuts; set aside.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
A glaze of 2 cups powdered sugar and a little milk may be spread on top of the two cooled loaves, if desired.

title: stage coach inn hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add to 3 1/2 cups boiling water.
Cook briefly until it thickens.
Add butter to taste.
When cool, roll into logs and deep fry until golden brown.

title: orange cottage salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Drain fruit.
Add to cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add broken up noodles and almonds. Saute until just beginning to brown.
Add sunflower seeds and cook until all is nicely toasted brown. Drain and set aside.
Toss shredded cabbage and scallions in a large bowl.
Mix dressing with whisk by blending red wine vinegar, sugar and oil. Pour into container. Right before serving, toss cabbage, nut mixture and dressing.

title: pan-fried apples
directions: Heat fat or oil in heavy frypan over low heat.
Add prepared apples; sprinkle with lemon juice and sugar.
Brown lightly, then turn once.
If apples are not tender after second side is browned, cover and cook a few minutes longer.
Makes 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill, then add crushed ice before serving.

title: grape ice cream
directions: Mix the cream, grape juice and sugar together and stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Add fresh lemon or lime juice to taste. Freeze in a hand cranked or electric ice cream freezer.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and Kool-Aid using just enough warm water to dissolve.
Mix sugar/Kool-Aid mixture with pineapple juice and grape juice.
Pour equally into 2 plastic gallon containers. Finish filling each container with water.
Shake well to mix. Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw until slushy.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale to each gallon when serving.

title: chili con carne
directions: Fry ground beef until done.
Add the rest of ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the Velveeta shells and cheese as directed, then add chunked chicken and serve.

title: lemony cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth. Add eggs and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Spread strawberry preserves evenly over prepared crust.
Pour cheese mixture over preserves. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and chill thoroughly.

title: country congealed vegetable salad
directions: Combine gelatin, dissolved in watah with vinegar, lemun juice, sugah, pimento, salt, cabbage, mater juice, bell pepper, celery and onion.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Melt shortening; add onion and celery.
Simmer 15 minutes over low heat.
Pour over bread crumbs, which have been mixed with other ingredients.
Add water; mix thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: snickers cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour in half of batter and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter and milk in medium saucepan, stir constantly. Pour over partially baked cake.
Sprinkle one package chocolate chips over caramel.
Pour on remaining cake batter.
Sprinkle with second package chocolate chips.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cake looks done.
Chips won't melt all the way.

title: broiled open-faced hamburger sandwiches
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and spread on split hamburger buns.
Broil open-faced for a few minutes until hamburger is done.
Watch carefully.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vicky's 7-layer dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning. Spread on bottom of 9-inch quiche dish. Layer remaining ingredients over bean mixture. Refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and spaghetti together in boiling water on stove for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain. Put in a 2-quart casserole; add soup, 1/2 of cheese, milk and 1/2 of onions.
Stir to combine.
Put remaining cheese and onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter; mix with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one.
Add flour slowly to mixture.
Stir in chips. Spread on a large cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: florida steak
directions: Put all ingredients together on cookie sheet or pan; pat thin. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.
Dust or dip in flour. Brown in skillet in bacon fat.
Place in shallow pan.
Pour 2 cans golden mushroom soup over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple, marshmallows, Cool Whip and pecans together.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cupcakes(and frosting)
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening; gradually add brown sugar, beating until light.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs (one at a time) beating until fluffy.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating after each addition.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix and spread between 3 packages of party rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients into a casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on baking sheet until light brown (about 5 minutes).
Remove crust from oven.

title: mex-italian lasagna
directions: Mix together the chili, salsa, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Mix together the Ricotta cheese and dried parsley.

title: broccoli medley
directions: Wash and cut all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over vegetables and chill for several hours or overnight.
Garnish with bacon bits when ready to serve.

title: nighty-nites
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 1/2 hour.
Beat egg whites until stiff (forms peaks).
Add sugar; continue to beat.
Fold in walnuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased nonstick or foil covered cookie sheets.
Put cookies in oven and turn oven off.
Leave overnight.
Don't peek! Makes 24.

title: dave maynard meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Flatten out on waxed paper with rolling pin.
Cover flattened ingredients with a layer of boiled ham.
Then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over ham.
Roll everything together like a jelly roll; seal ends tightly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brats "wisconsin style"
directions: Empty beer in saucepan.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Bring to boil for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: In double boiler, heat Jell-O, water, cream cheese and marshmallows, then add other ingredients.
Pour into dish and congeal.

title: plantation light corn bread
directions: Mix.
Pour into loaf pan prepared with Pam.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Beat
peanut butter and 1/4 cup milk with rotary beater until smooth.
Slowly
add remaining milk, beating until well blended. Add
pudding mix;
blend well, about 1 minute.
Pour into serving dishes; chill.
Or beat at lowest speed on mixer.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Mix broth and
cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, buttermilk and margarine.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave herbed potatoes and onions
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Thinly slice potatoes and onion.
Layer half the potatoes and half the onion in a microwavable dish.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and pepper. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Repeat the potato, onion, seasoning and margarine.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 12 minutes or until potatoes are soft, turning dish once.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare the cake according to directions, making 2 layers. Split both layers.
Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut and chill.
Spread all but one cup of mixture between the 4 layers.
Blend the rest with whipped cream and spread on cake. Refrigerate for 3 days in airtight container.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Break up lettuce.
Slice onion.
Break up bacon and cauliflower.
Put all ingredients in layers in large, covered bowl. Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Put this mixture over top of vegetables.
Set overnight in refrigerator. Mix well before serving.

title: m and m  cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs, and vanilla. Sift flour, soda, and salt. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix well. Add half the M & M candies and save rest to decorate the tops. Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet and bake 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spanish corn bread
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour into hot greased 8-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: golden baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Remove skin from chicken.
Place in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 9-inch round baking dish.
Spread 1 teaspoon butter on each piece; sprinkle with onion, garlic salt and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.
"A great weight watcher meal."

title: microwave enchilada casserole
directions: Crumble beef into a 2-quart glass container.
Add onion and garlic.
Mix lightly.
Place in microwave and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Drain meat mixture and then stir.
Microwave on High for 2 more minutes.
Stir in Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies and taco seasoning.
Cook on High for 3 minutes and remove from microwave.

title: corn bread(lite)
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir to mix.
Add buttermilk and oil. Mix well.
Bake at 350° until brown, for 50 to 60 minutes in greased loaf pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix gently together and put in buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Toss all other ingredients (except crab) into cream cheese mixture and combine.
Gently mix crab evenly into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: taco pie
directions: Saute meat with onion, salt, pepper, water and seasoning mix. Cook on low heat 10 minutes.
Put 1/2 meat mixture on top of tortillas.
Top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Follow with remaining meat and top off with the last of the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: apple salad
directions: When jello begins to jell, stir in apples, celery and nuts. You may want to double this recipe, it's so good.

title: dried beef log
directions: Blend cream cheese and horseradish. Stir in olives.
On waxed paper, shape mixture in 2 (6-inch) rolls.
Wrap and chill several hours.
Roll in beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: raisin-nut pie(good!)
directions: Mix ingredients and fill unbaked pie shell half full.
Bake at 375° about 20 to 25 minutes.
(Be sure not to overcook as will become hard and too chewy!)
Best served hot.

title: gratin of winter squash
directions: A one-pound squash yields 2 cups cooked pulp.

title: soda cracker crunch
directions: Spread crackers in single layer on foil lined 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan (or cookie sheet which has sides).
Boil sugar and butter for 3 minutes; spread on top of crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes, or until crackers float to top, at 400°.
Put chocolate chips on top while bars are still hot.
Spread chips smoothly when melted.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Let set or refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Remove from foil and break into pieces.

title: butterscotch babble
directions: Night before:
Grease tube or Bundt pan.
Mix dry ingredients. Starting with dry, layer with dough ending with dry.
Put margarine pats on top.
Cover tightly with foil; leave on counter overnight to rise.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chocolate; let cool.
Cream butter and vanilla.
Add brown sugar; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Spoon in the 2 tablespoons flour.
Add salt and soda; mix together.
Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture; mix well.
Blend in chocolate, water and sour cream. Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add rest of ingredients and mix together. Add water to desired consistency. Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Mix sugar, salt, water and honey in saucepan and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Stir until thick and creamy.
Turn out on waxed paper.
Separate with 2 forks.
Makes about 1/2 pound.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add
sugar and Crisco oil.
Mix together.
Add vanilla, grated zucchini, flour, baking soda, baking powder,
salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add extra for flavoring 1 cup nuts or 1 cup raisins.
Grease and flour bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream the butter or oleo, eggs and sugar. Add nuts and bananas. Sift flour and soda. Add to mixture.
Put in loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: fruit crush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from fire, stir in juices and bananas and freeze.
Take out 1 hour before serving and pour ginger ale over.
Serves 24 people or makes 6 quarts.

title: eggs augustus
directions: Combine eggs, cream, melted butter, flour and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Pour into greased 10-inch pan.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: cranberry meat loaf(serves 6)
directions: Oil a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle bottom with brown sugar and spread with cranberry sauce.
In large bowl, pour cold water over stuffing mix and toss with fork.
Add onion, green pepper, egg, salt and ground meat to stuffing and mix well.
Spoon gently over cranberry sauce in pan.
(Do not pack down, but spread out to all corners, sealing in cranberries.)

title: apple crumb squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except applesauce and nuts.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup of oats mixture.
Press remaining oats mixture onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes; cool. Spread applesauce over partially baked crust.
Sprinkle with nuts. Sprinkle reserved 1 cup of oats mixture over top.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Best kept in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 24 squares.

title: sweet potatoes with apricots and pecans
directions: Bring 1 cup apricot juice, sugar, salt, cinnamon, orange peel and cornstarch to boil, stirring until thickened.
Add butter, apricots and pecans.
Pour over sweet potatoes in greased dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add all other ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Add 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Mix. Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle rest of chips over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter crisps
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Heat over low flame.
Add peanut butter; continue to heat while stirring.
Pour mixture over cereal and chips.
Stir until well coated.
Stir into pan; cool and cut into bars.
May be dusted with powdered sugar.

title: gnocchis(from the kitchen of sarah surina.)
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel and mash while warm and blend with flour.
Add slightly beaten egg, yolk, butter and salt.
Place on board and knead lightly.
Keep dough soft.
Roll into sticks 1-inch thick and about 10-inches long.
Cut into 3/4-inch pieces. Dent in the middle with a fork.
Boil in salted water.
Cook until they rise to the top of the water.
Drain.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve chilled over fresh spinach.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook bell pepper and onion in butter in microwave.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add rice.
Let sit, covered, for 5 minutes. Add soup and corn.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Cook 30 minutes, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350°.

title: creole corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add to other ingredients.
Season to taste. Bake in greased baking dish at 325° for an hour.
Especially good with fried chicken.

title: beet pickles(from the files of norma brown)
directions: Mix all ingredients (except beets) together and bring to a boil.
Pour over beets in jars and seal.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Blend well and refrigerate.
The longer the better, at least 1 hour before.
Serve warm or cold.

title: almond-ham roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ham, stirring until blended. Spread 1 tablespoon of mixture on each ham slice.
Roll up, starting at short side; wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill 1 hour and slice in 3/4-inch pieces.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with half of Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: grandma's apple cake
directions: In medium bowl, stir together the eggs, sugar, oil, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, vanilla and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Mix apples into batter.
In ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spoon batter into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Sprinkle cake with confectioners sugar.

title: cold water dill pickles
directions: Full strength cider vinegar from health store is best.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Cut ham and green onions into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into a ball; garnish with 1 package of Eckrich chopped ham, cut into small pieces.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken and vegetable stir fry
directions: Heat a large, heavy skillet or wok over high heat until water sizzles when dropped onto the metal. Add 1 1/2 Tbsp. of the oil and tilt the pan gently in all directions until the oil has coated the surface. When the oil is hot (not to the point of smoking), add chicken and stir fry for 2 minutes. Remove the chicken to a bowl. Add remaining oil to the skillet. When hot, add the frozen vegetable mix and stir fry for about 4 minutes, until the larger pieces are cooked through. Return chicken to the skillet, add the water and soy sauce, and stir fry for an additional 2 minutes. Add spinach. Cover and steam over medium heat for 2 minutes. Using tongs, turn the spinach once, so that it heats evenly; cover and steam for an additional 2 minutes. Remove chicken and vegetables with slotted spoon. Spoon the liquid into small bowls and serve as a gravy or dip. This has 7 grams carbohydrate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Mix grated cheese, sausage and Bisquick until Bisquick is mixed well.
Make into small balls and bake on a cookie sheet (ungreased) for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except cranberries and nuts, in electric mixer until well blended.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until they thicken slightly.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add cream cheese and butter alternately with remaining sugar, beating constantly.
Beat in lemon rind and vanilla.
Fold in flour until just combined. Stir in 1/3 of egg whites and fold in remainder.

title: 15-minute chocolate-banana cream pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pie filling mix, whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla on low speed until blended.
Increase speed and beat until very thick, about 3 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into crust.
Layer slices of bananas on top (save 1 banana for the top).
Pour remaining filling into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with sliced bananas and additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture.
Dip in Crisco.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then turn chicken over and let cook for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly sweet potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine; add flour and pecans. Mix and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Make in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Grease pan.
Can be prepared the night before and refrigerated.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: Put dry ingredients in large flat boiler.
Add milk and eggs; heat slowly until mixture starts to thicken.
Turn off heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture over wafers and sliced bananas in casserole dish.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add orange sherbet.
Whip with wire whisk.
Add Mandarin oranges and pineapple tidbits.
Chill until set.

title: cranberry salad (donna's)
directions: Dissolved jello in hot water, stir in the rest of the ingredients. Chill until till firm.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli in bowl.
Fry, drain and crumble bacon.
Combine bacon, raisins, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and onion; mix well. Pour mixture over broccoli.
Toss lightly.
Serve.

title: mom's pot roast
directions: Brown roast on all sides in pan on top of stove.
Then add onion soup mix, tenderizer and water.
Cook 1 hour.
Add chopped vegetables.
Cook 1 1/2 hours more or until roast and vegetables are tender.

title: double layer sweet potato pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in a large bowl. Beat with wire whisk, until smooth.
Stir in cool whip.
Spread mixture on top of crust.
Pour cold milk into large bowl; add sweet potatoes, pudding mix and spices.
Beat with wire whisk until well mixed. Mixture will be thick.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with cool whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: slushy punch
directions: In a large pan bring water to boil.
Add Jell-O and mix until dissolved.
Bring to boil and add sugar and water.
Cool down, then add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir well; freeze in large plastic containers.
When ready to use, remove from freezer 4 to 5 hours to thaw.
Add ginger ale; mix.
It will be slushy. Can be refrozen.
Serves 50.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan.

title: hubbel house dressing
directions: Chop onion and pepper fine.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, strain and cool.
Add this to one quart (like Kraft) salad dressing.
Good.

title: baked pheasant, quail or dove
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Roll fowl pieces (or breasts) in flour and season.
Saute in frying pan until golden brown.
Remove fowl to small roaster or flat casserole.
To skillet drippings, add 1 can mushroom soup, chicken rice soup, sherry and sliced green onions. Heat and pour over fowl.
Cover roasting pan and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove fowl to platter.
To sauce in roaster, add additional can of mushroom soup, drained whole mushrooms and thin with sherry to the proper consistency for gravy.
Serve with Uncle Ben's long grain and wild rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken tidbits
directions: Cut each dry thigh into 8 pieces.
Refrigerate 8 hours. Combine butter, honey, and teriyaki sauce in a small pan.
Stir well; bring to a boil.
Remove and set aside.
Sprinkle pieces with salts and pepper.
Dip pieces into honey mixture, then coat with seed.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, turning once.

title: vanilla brownies
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar with a wooden spoon.
With spoon beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a 1 pint measuring cup; stir.
Add to butter mixture; add nuts if desired.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan (mixture will be stiff).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut bars while still warm.

title: creamed chicken and rice
directions: Cover chicken with water; boil choice cuts of chicken in salted water until tender.
Do not overcook.
Remove skin from chicken and discard.
Add cream, butter, salt and pepper to broth. Thicken with flour paste.
Cook until thickened.
Place chicken pieces around rice.
Pour sauce over rice and chicken.
Serves 8.

title: cream pineapple pie
directions: Cook and stir constantly until thick.
Set aside to cool. Whip a large can of Carnation milk that has been in freezer for 1 hour.
Add cool mixture to whipped milk; pour into cookie or graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add 5 egg yolks, one at a time. Add dry ingredients, buttermilk, coconut and nuts.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch or 2 smaller pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cake must be kept refrigerated. Frost with the following:

title: "big mac" cookies
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Brush egg white on top, then sprinkle with sesame seed.
Kids and adults love these.

title: peach shortcake
directions: Slice peaches and
add	sugar
to
taste.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. When ready
to
serve,
spoon peaches over cake slices and top with Cool Whip.

title: potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Cook over medium heat, stirring carefully with pancake turner, about 5 minutes or until potatoes are heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Sprinkle with dill.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Roll into small balls. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: golden glow casserole
directions: Add corn meal gradually to boiling salted water, stirring constantly; cook over boiling water 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour into shallow pan.
When cold, cut into 1 inch squares.
Melt cheese on top of double boiler.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly. Arrange layers of mush and cheese in casserole; bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Mix egg, milk, 2/3 cup crumbs and pimentos.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Toss melted butter with remaining crumbs.
Sprinkle on top corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies into large Pyrex dish.
Pour melted margarine over cookies and set aside to cool.

title: do ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add butter and cream cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Gradually stir in 1 to 2 cups milk to a nice consistency.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Put milk in saucepan.
Add margarine and sugar.
Heat until margarine melts. Cool slightly.
Add yeast dissolved in water. Then add well beaten eggs and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat hard and set aside to rise.
Stir down and add rest of flour. Then when blended, turn onto floured board and knead lightly.
Not too much flour, dough should be soft, not stiff.
Divide and shape into type rolls you wish.
Place on greased pans and let rise until very, very light.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts and sugar.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch floured and greased pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together.
Sprinkle chopped almonds on top.
Heat in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt ottye's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add extracts.
Stir in 1 egg at a time. Beat well after each.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.*
Roll in sugar, flatten and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add taco mix as directed. Drain.
Mix other ingredients in.

title: angel's pot pie
directions: Put 1 crust in deep-dish pie pan.
Combine Veg-All, chicken, onions, bell peppers, celery, soup, black pepper and garlic powder in bowl.
Pour into pie crust; cover with other pie crust.
Make 3 slits in top crust.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes (or until golden brown).

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour; mix until all the flour is moistened.
This is an easy crust to handle and can be rolled without toughening.
Makes 2 double crust pies.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg whites.
Add sugar and salt. Slowly melt margarine in three-quart casserole.
Mix nuts into egg white mixture.
Bake nuts in margarine at 325° until margarine is absorbed, about 45 minutes.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: In large pot, combine oil and flour for roux.
Cook slowly on medium burner for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roux will be medium brown. Add coarsely chopped onions, bell pepper and celery and saute until tender.
Add okra which has been chopped and smothered down, and several cups of water.
Simmer for approximately 30 minutes. Add salt, red pepper and black pepper to taste.
Add shrimp, crab meat, and green onions and simmer for another 30 minutes. Serve over steaming rice.
Add file if desired.

title: spiced rutabagas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sugar and cook, uncovered, an additional 20 minutes or until rutabaga is tender, stirring occasionally. Transfer to a serving bowl; sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings (37 calories and 5% fat per 1/2 cup serving).

title: apple squares
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and Crisco to make crust. Knead and divide into two sections of dough.
Roll one ball of dough on very large cookie sheet; stretch to edges of pan.
Fill with apples and cup of sugar if needed and cinnamon or nutmeg. Place top crust over apples and pull to edge. Brush with egg water mixture and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: gobs
