directions: Cream
together
sugar, Crisco, eggs, milk, vanilla and boiling water.
Sift together in another bowl the flour, soda, salt,
baking
powder
and	cocoa.	Add
alternately to sugar. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425°.
Cool, then add icing and wrap.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Sift flour, cut in shortening until small size, stir in egg, add milk, a tablespoon at a time.
Mixing thoroughly to form a soft dough, form 1-inch balls and roll in sesame seed.
Flatten a little and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal, vinegar and butter together well and add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix together well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 325°
for approximately 50 minutes. Delicious and rich!

title: turkey burgers
directions: Form 4 patties.
Broil 7 minutes, turning once or fry in pan using nonstick cooking spray.
Serve on bun with your favorite condiments.

title: glazed rutabaga
directions: Steam or boil rutabaga until tender, about 15 minutes.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and heat until blended. Add drained rutabaga and simmer until rutabaga is glazed.

title: sweet and sour pork stir-fry
directions: Brown the pork in a wok or over the stove.
When almost done, add the onions and peppers.
Stir-fry until onions are tender. Add catsup, honey, wine, soy sauce and seasoning together, then add to pork mixture.
Simmer until mixture thickens and flavors unite.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.
This is also good with chicken, cubed beef and meatballs.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions.
Cool; cut into 1-inch squares.
Make pudding according to directions. In a clear glass bowl, layer half of the cake, strawberries, bananas, pudding, glaze, nuts and Cool Whip.
Repeat layer, using other half of ingredients.
Garnish with berries.
Looks pretty and is delicious.

title: caramel chews
directions: Place caramels and cream in top of double boiler over hot water and heat until caramels melt, stirring occasionally.
Toss together remaining ingredients and pour over caramel mixture.
Mix thoroughly, working rapidly, and drop on wax paper.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: brownies
directions: Stir all the ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: fruit burst cookies
directions: Beat butter sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in almond extract.

Combine flour and salt; add to mixture and blend well. Shape level tablespoonfuls of dough into balls; roll in nuts. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten sightly. Indent centers; fill with fruit spread.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or just until lightly browned.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: vermicelli spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, celery, green pepper, and onions together.
Add vermicelli and mix thoroughly.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, and salt.
Add to other mixture and stir to mix.
Make one day ahead.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium size bowl, put egg yolks, slightly beaten, milk and lemon juice. Stir only until blended and thickened.
Pour in pie shell.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix well with all other ingredients.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator.
Take out as needed.
Roll thin and cut in biscuits.
Bake in hot oven (350° to 400°).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, including sugar into mixing bowl.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together until smooth.
Portion into 3 conventional bread pans. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until done.
Freezes well.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour remaining batter on top. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat puffs
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add onions, soy sauce, ketchup and allspice and cook on medium until onions are clear, mixing all the ingredients in the process.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.
Allow mixture to cool for 10 minutes.

title: cherry cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Add cranberries.
Let chill and mix in Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in mold or bowl until firm.

title: hot ham buns
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed and onions.
Spread on one side of buns.
Put a slice each of ham and cheese on each bun. Arrange on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes until hot.

title: aunt bertie's 7-up cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy (approximately 20 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add lemon extract; then add flour and 7-Up alternately.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a Bundt pan.
Do not open door of oven while baking.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Fill a large pot 3/4 full with water.
Clean chicken and place in clear water.
Cook slowly, skimming the top until clear.
Wash and cut all vegetables.
Add seasoning and vegetables to broth and cook until tender.
Remove chicken.
Bone, shred and replace in broth to continue simmering.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions together until done.
Drain.
Set aside.

title: carrot rice bake
directions: In saucepan, bring water, bouillon granules and salt to boiling.
Stir in carrot, rice, butter and thyme.
Return to boiling.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 325° for 25 minutes; stir.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, about 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, water and salt until clear.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in pie shell. Top with 1/2 pint of Cool Whip.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Combine beaten eggs, milk, cheese, salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Place sausage and bread cubes in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over sausage and bread cubes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable oil spray.
Slice bread into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place bread tightly together in one layer.
Beat eggs lightly.
Add milk, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix with whisk.
Pour 1/2 liquid over bread.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Place on top of bread to cover.
Pour remaining egg mixture over apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar (or less) with cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with syrup.
If prepared night before, cover, refrigerate and bake for 50 minutes.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs, add oil, mix in bisquick and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13 ungreased pan and bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cabbage slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Finely chop onion and celery.
Mix together in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Pour over veggies and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together butter or oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Toss with Crispix cereal.
When cereal is well coated, put in large paper bag with powdered sugar and shake until coated. Spread on cookie sheet until chocolate is set.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Divide into 3 balls.
Roll to size of your choice. Wrap in foil.
Leave in icebox overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Open one end of the foil.
Pour out excess grease and cool. Serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs.
Add pumpkin and water.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt, baking powder and spices. Stir in dates and nuts.
Bake in preheat-heated 350 degree oven for one hour.
Makes 2 or 3 small loaves.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, reserving 1/2 cup of flour to dust nuts and apples.
Bake in an 8 x 11-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for about 40 minutes or until done.
(A tube pan can be used for this recipe.)

title: alan okada's best ever gingerbread cookies(merry christmas!)
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter or margarine, sugar and salt.
Stir in eggs, molasses and vinegar.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients to molasses mixture, gradually, and mix well.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: deep dish fruit pie
directions: Butter a deep baking dish.
Put the fruit in the bottom. Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and the flour; spread over fruit.
Mix the remaining ingredients; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
If the top browns too quickly, cover with aluminum foil during the last 10 to 20 minutes.

title: stewed chicken with dumplings
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, heat oil and brown chicken.
Drain off fat.
Add water, celery rib, lemon, salt, thyme, pepper, bay leaf and onions.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat and simmer, covered, 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Discard chicken skin, celery rib, lemon and bay leaf.
Bring broth to a boil.
Gradually add dumplings (noodles), carrots and sliced celery.
Boil, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes until noodles and vegetables are tender.
Blend flour into 3 tablespoons water.
Stir into broth.
Cook and stir 1 minute. Remove chicken from bones and cut into pieces.
Add to dumplings mixture and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage 'n beans country style
directions: Cook sausage in skillet, breaking up with a fork as it cooks. Saute onion with the sausage.
Drain all fat.
Combine beans, catsup, mustard, poultry seasoning with the sausage and onion.
Mix well.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions. Put corn muffin mix into a greased 2-quart casserole dish, making a nest in the center.
Spoon meat mixture into nest.
When it's cooked, it makes a sort of crust around the other mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Garnish with parsley, tomato slices, catsup or whatever you like.
Recipe can be increased to suit your family size or for guests.
"We like it warmed over, too!"

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into thin pieces.
Cook potatoes until semi-tender.
Mix milk, onions and soup in a bowl.
Layer potatoes, soup mixture, cheese and butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: steamers
directions: Brown ground beef with green pepper and onion.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Add chili sauce and cook on medium for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook medium head of cabbage in salt water until tender. Drain after done.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Pour undiluted cream of chicken soup over cabbage.
Add 1 1/2 cups of grated cheese.
Add Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: dill veggie dip and chips
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for 1 hour and store in an airtight container.
Keeps for 1 week.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a small pan melt 2 tablespoons margarine over medium heat. Add celery and onion.
Cook, stirring about 3 minutes, until tender.
Set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
In another bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Boil water and alternate the dry ingredients with water while mixing.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Into large casserole or Dutch oven, layer potatoes, margarine, onions, cheese slices, grated cheese and parsley.
Lightly sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers to within 1 to 1 1/2-inches of top of pan.
Pour milk around and over the layers.

title: stir-fried pork in garlic sauce
directions: Slice pork across grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips; set aside. Combine next 3 ingredients; add pork, stirring until well coated. Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour oils around the top of a preheated wok, coating sides.
Allow to heat at medium (325°) for 1 minute. Add pork; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes or until browned.
Remove pork; add mushrooms, onions, water chestnuts, garlic and pepper. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add pork and cook an additional 2 minutes.

title: ginger crisps
directions: Sift together flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Cream lard
and the 1 cup sugar.
Add egg, molasses and water; beat
thoroughly.
Stir
sifted
dry
ingredients into creamed mixture,
mixing
well.
Shape
dough into balls about the size of a
small walnut and roll in 1/3 cup sugar.
Place on a cookie sheet
about
2 inches apart.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: orange pineapple ice box cake
directions: Bake one angel food cake and slice into 3 layers.
Cook for 5 minutes the juice of 2 oranges (1/2 cup), 1/2 cup sugar and 1 1/2 cup crushed pineapple.
Dissolve 1 package Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup of water and add gelatine mixture to pineapple mixture while still hot.
When almost cold, add 2 beaten egg yolks.
Place in refrigerator and let thicken.
When thick and cold, add 1-8 oz container of Cool Whip.
Spread between layers of cake, then on top and sides.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: apple nobby cake
directions: Pare apples and diced into 1/4-inch cubes.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold with or without whipped cream or ice cream.
Freezes well.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Blend until smooth.
Cut bread into 2-inch rounds (you should get two per slice).
Lightly butter wheat round.
Spread white round with cream cheese mixture.
Place cucumber between slices. Garnish can be added to top: baby shrimp, pimento, sliced olives, etc.
Serve immediately or cover tightly and refrigerate.
Makes 10 appetizer sandwiches.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Grease a Bundt pan well.
Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom. Place rolls (frozen) in pan.
Will make about 1 layer.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top of rolls.
Sprinkle pudding mix over brown sugar; add cinnamon.
Cut the butter in little pieces and place evenly on top of other ingredients.
Cover with waxed paper and let rise on kitchen counter overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside-down on plate to allow syrup to run into rolls.

title: grandma monahan's banana bread
directions: Grease bread pan and preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Mash bananas and add ingredients in order listed into a large mixing bowl.
Stir well until all blended.
Bake in a preheated oven for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Test middle with a knife.
(Keep moist; don't overbake.)
(Ripe bananas can be frozen and kept until ready.)

title: snowballs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll into small balls.
Then roll them in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta with spinach and garlic
directions: Cook spinach in microwave according to directions on box. Meanwhile, melt margarine and add minced garlic.
Saute approximately 5 minutes.
Add cooked spinach, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach mixture to cooked pasta. Stir well.
Add grated cheese to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Makes 2 small balls or 1 large ball.

title: confetti mold(serves a bunch)
directions: Make cherry, lime and orange jello according to package directions.
(At Christmastime, you can use another cherry or lime instead of the orange.)
Chill each box until firmly set in an ice cube tray or other shallow pan.

title: tarragon beef brisket
directions: Place meat on heavy foil in baking dish.
Place soup mix and water on top and seal the foil tightly.
Bake 300° for 3 hours. Refrigerate overnight (or several hours until meat is cool and easy to carve).
Pour juices into container and save.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, vanilla, brown sugar and melted butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Press on cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and butter; pour over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening and chocolate together. Blend eggs and sugar and stir into chocolate mix.
Beat in combined dried ingredients.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into log.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Slice and serve.
(They're similar to Reese's peanut butter cups!)

title: zucchini patties
directions: Beat egg, add grated zucchini, cheese, Bisquick and seasoning. Mixture will be sticky.
Shape into patties 3 inches in diameter. Drop gently into skillet which has 1/2 inch hot oil.
Flatten as patties begin to fry.
Cook until lightly brown, drain on paper towel.

title: kay's pirogi
directions: Mix flour, eggs and salt together.
Gradually add water until you have a soft, but not sticky, dough.
Knead it until it blisters.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with glass into circles.
Place teaspoonful of filling on circles.
(Before placing filling on dough, take a salt shaker and shake salt all over dough lightly; this helps when pinching pirogi to seal.)
Pinch edges to keep filling from escaping.
Drop into boiling salted water until pirogi rise to the top or about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter and brown.
(We also add chopped onions in this butter.) Pour over pirogi and toss to mix.

title: torte
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, add cream of tartar and sugar slowly.
Fold in crackers and nuts.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread Dream Whip on top with cherries.
Chill 5 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In a 15 x 10-inch baking dish, combine butter and onion.
Bake uncovered at 400° until onion is pale gold.
Stir occasionally.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in butter.
Remove excess grease.
Add soup and water.
Add sliced onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until chops are tender, about 1 hour.

title: tasty stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; cut piece from stem end and remove seeds. Parboil 5 minutes in a little water.
Drain.
Stuff with mixture of corned beef hash, rice, dried onion soup mix and catsup; top with buttered crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Pour in enough hot water to cover bottom of pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Add sugar and syrup together in pan; bring to a boil.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Stir and drop on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: golden hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls into a hot deep fryer.
Turn to brown both sides evenly.
Eat while hot. Serves four people for a meal.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cream cheese.
Will be very thin.
Pour can of chili over cheese and sprinkle with Monterey Jack and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: persimmon or pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix together first five ingredients and set aside.
Beat sugar, margarine, persimmon or pumpkin, egg and soda thoroughly.
Mix flour mixture in, then add nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen. Best to use dates that have no sugar on them already.

title: chicken with dijon creamed shallot sauce
directions: Salt and pepper the chicken breasts.
Heat butter in saute pan.
Add breasts.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes on one side.
Turn over and cook 8 minutes more.
Transfer breasts to a warm platter and set aside.
Add shallots to pan and cook 30 seconds.
Add wine and cook 1 minute.
Add heavy cream and reduce to 3/4 cup.
Stir in mustard and return breasts to pan.
Bring sauce to a boil.
Serve hot and garnish with chives.

title: lee's souffled mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut out mushroom stems.
Melt butter in medium-sized skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, cavity down, and cook until lightly brown (2 to 3 minutes), turning once.

Place mushrooms, cavity up, on baking sheet and fill each with one rounded tablespoon of souffle. Top with 1/2 teaspoon cheese (each) and sprinkle with paprika. Bake until souffle is puffy and set, about 16 minutes.
Or fill and refrigerate until ready to cook.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add sour cream and soup to chopped chicken.
Mix and put in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix with Ritz cracker crumbs. Put on top of chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: leftover cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat 2 egg whites that are at room temperature until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat again until stiff.
Fold in mini chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto pan.
Put in oven.
Switch oven off! Leave pan of cookies in oven overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salt and water until tender.
Drain.
Mash with fork.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix squash, onion, milk, crackers and eggs.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee toffee pie
directions: Shell:
Crumble crust mix very fine; blend in brown sugar, nuts and 1 square of chocolate (grated).
Remove 1 tablespoon of the mixture and place in a pan and bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Cool.
Add water to the remaining mixture.
Blend well and press into an 8-inch buttered pie pan.
Moisten fingers for pressing. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: hot fudge topping for ice cream
directions: Blend sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add boiling water and butter. Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
When done, add vanilla.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Dissolve jello in hot water and strawberry soda.
Poke holes in cake. Pour mixture over cake. Chill.

title: hepburn's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat like mad.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Mix well and dump into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes in a 325° oven.
Remove and allow to cool for a while, then cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: ladyfinger cheesecake
directions: (Chill beaters and bowl prior to starting this recipe for best results!)

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all together and put in baking dish.
Pour in 1/2 cup water.
Take one package of cake mix.
Sprinkle over Jell-O mixture.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Pour evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molded lobster crabmeat salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water; dissolve with boiling water.
Add lemon juice and when it begins to thicken, add fish, celery, apples and nuts.
Then fold in mayonnaise to which the whipped cream has been added.
Pour into mold.
Serve on bed of lettuce and garnish with stuffed olives and quarters of hard-boiled eggs or slices of tomato.

title: country company potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes until soft.
Peel and then grate.
Heat margarine, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Add sour cream and pour over potatoes; mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with enough crushed cornflakes with butter to cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Stir together biscuit mix, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Fold in zucchini.
In skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Use 2 tablespoons mixture for each fritter.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes on each side until brown.
Yields 8 to 10 fritters.

title: pineapple-lemon dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with crumbs and sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: kisses(cookies)
directions: Beat ingredients together for 20 minutes or until stiff.
Fold in 1 cup walnuts or chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on trays. Instead of nuts or chips you can use food coloring, a few drops with small bowls of mixture (example: small margarine bowl).
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until they come off tray easy.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it forms a firm ball in cold water.
Remove from
heat and add next 3 ingredients.
Stir until chocolate chips and hipolite dissolve.
Beat fudge about 10 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch lof pan.
Cool and score.

title: de "lows" bread pudding
directions: Toast bread before making bread crumbs.
(This is the secret for making good bread pudding.)
Scald milk and pour over bread crumbs. Cool and add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into an 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Combine orange juice, salt and ginger in small pan.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in diced oranges.
Pour over hot carrots; toss to coat.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon margarine to each serving.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine ingredients.
Stir by hand until well mixed. Pour into pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: almond puffs
directions: Boil butter, water, salt and sugar. Add flour; beat over low heat until smooth. Stir to cool off of heat. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add raisins. Drop on greased cooking sheet. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: squash maximilian
directions: Cut squash into pieces; boil in unsalted water.
Drain completely.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Brown onion rings in some of the bacon drippings.
In a greased casserole, make layers, beginning with drained squash, crumbled bacon, onion rings and cheese cubes.
Repeat layers, then top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: quick salad
directions: Spoon Cool Whip into larger bowl.
Sprinkle lime Jell-O over Cool Whip.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Chill and it's ready to serve.

title: mallynda's rolled chicken breasts
directions: Cut chicken in half; pound each until thin.
Place one slice of ham or cheese (or both) on chicken and roll up.
Stick a toothpick into chicken to keep together.
Roll into flour mix.
In frypan melt butter or margarine.
Place chicken in pan until brown.
Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken; cook for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop onion, bread and green pepper, then mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: blender coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all together in blender and then pour into 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter buddy bars
directions: In a large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour. Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brown.
Shut oven off. Immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over top; place back in oven until chips are shiny.
Spread them evenly over top.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: grape juice
directions: Have grapes washed and all bad grapes taken out.
Place the ingredients in quart jars.	Fill jars with boiling water. Put on new lids and process in hot water bath 20 minutes.	Hot water bath should be filled to neck of jar.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Add vanilla and sugar gradually.
Fold in chocolate mini chips.
Drop on paper bag by teaspoonful.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
They will be slightly browned.
Let cool before removing from bag.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine (al dente) in lightly salted water.
Finely chop parsley, onion and garlic and saute in olive oil until tender and lightly browned.
Open clams and strain into container, saving the juice.
Set juice aside to settle.
Add clams to this pan to heat but not cook.
Add clam juice to the mixture to heat but not cook. Serve over linguine topped with liberal amounts of Romano cheese.

title: hush puppies
directions: Make corn bread (not too thick).
Add chopped green onion.
Add corn.
Add hot sauce.
Drop in hot oil, very hot, 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Save 1 cup of mix for icing.
Put mixture between each layer.

title: elegantly scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and cut up.
In a saucepan over low heat, combine shredded Cheddar cheese and butter.
Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes and turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Refrigerate.
To serve, return to room temperature and bake 25 minutes at 450° or until heated through.

title: mushroom pork chops
directions: Place seasoned chops in casserole dish.
Combine soup with water.
Mix and pour over chops.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 1 hour with cover on.
Mix halfway through cooking time.
Brown with lid off for 10 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable platter
directions: Cook 4 cups assorted fresh vegetables in boiling water until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain thoroughly; marinate several hours in French dressing.
Chill.
Serve drained vegetables chilled or at room temperature.

title: butter tarts
directions: Combine ingredients and fill tart shells.
Bake at 250° for 5 to 10 minutes, then at 350° until done.

title: french onion potato salad
directions: Boil water and add 1 teaspoon of salt to water with the potatoes. Boil potatoes for 8 to 10 minutes. After cooked, cool potatoes completely. Chop celery and onions along with 3 cooked eggs. Combine onion dip, brown sugar and remaining salt and pepper. Add potatoes, onion, celery and eggs to mixture. Chill overnight, then slice remaining egg on top to serve.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake the cake in two circular pans.
When cakes have cooled, divide the cakes in half (top and bottom, not two halves).
Place one layer of cake in a trifle bowl (or other large bowl).
Cover with half can of chocolate pudding, 1/4 of Heath bar brickles, Cool Whip and Hershey bar.
Repeat layers until you have four layers of everything.

title: crab balls
directions: Mix thoroughly and dip your Crab Balls for an excellent and exciting appetizer.

title: frozen amaretto creme
directions: Soften ice cream.
Combine ingredients.
Pour into cupcake papers.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Freeze.
Garnish with red cherries and green leaves.

title: john-michael's favorite sugar tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream together.
Add egg and mix. Sift soda and flour together and mix with butter, egg and sugar. Flatten a small ball of dough on floured board and roll thin.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake until golden brown in a 300° oven.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs; stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Mix and then add applesauce.
Do not overmix.
Fill paper muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in preheated oven at 375°.
Makes 36 muffins.
Batter keeps well in refrigerator for 4 to 6 weeks.
I add raisins and nuts.

title: skillet fudge
directions: Bring evaporated milk, sugar and salt to a boil in 10-inch skillet.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Combine marshmallows, chocolate bits and nuts.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Cool in skillet or pour into foil-lined, buttered 9-inch square pan and cool.
Makes for easy cutting into large squares.

title: cabbage rolls (haloopkies)
directions: Soften cabbage leaves and separate by placing cabbage core down in a large pot (cut through leaves as far as possible).
Cover with water and bring to a boil, remove each leaf as soon as it starts to wilt and place in pan.
Mix together rice, ground chuck, eggs and onion.

Place a portion of rice mixture into each loaf and roll up. Cut up cores of cabbages, put in bottom of a large pot, pack rolls in layers along with some more chopped onion and tomatoes and juice on each layer.
Cover with water, bring to a boil and reduce heat to medium.
Cook until done, 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with sauce.

title: chocolate pound cake with chocolate sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Then beat with mixer at "medium" for seven minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating each egg
only until yellow is gone.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to the above mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mix.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or loaf pans.
Do not fill pans over 3/4 full. Bake at 325° for 80 minutes for tube pan, 50 minutes for loaf pans.
Test for doneness.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in half.
Blend food color into one half.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each half into 4-inch rope.
For smooth, even ropes, roll them back and forth on lightly floured board.
Place ropes side by side; press on baking sheet.
Curve top of cookie down to form handle of cane.
Bake for about 9 minutes, or until set and very light brown, if you wish.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix all together and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Make out in small balls on cookie sheet, press with fork.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: caramel pecan dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix at highest speed until crumbly.
Press into prepared pan.
In small bowl, beat milk, 1 egg and vanilla until blended.
Stir in pecans and Bits O' Brickle chips.
Pour over base in pan; spread to cover.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until light golden brown.
Center may appear loose but will set upon cooling.
Allow to cool completely before cutting. Ingredients may be put together and make like a cake but requires longer to cook.

title: quick, lite italian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dressing on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Delicious served over rice.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Skin chicken pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chicken may be browned first, if desired.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over chicken in pan.
Sprinkle fresh or canned mushrooms on the last 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad 3
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough stalks at end and wash broccoli thoroughly.
Cut flowerets and stems into bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl.
Add bacon, onion and cheese.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add to broccoli mixture and toss gently.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Divide into 2 equal parts and form into loaves about 4 inches in diameter.
Wrap each loaf in heavy duty aluminum foil.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Place loaves, still wrapped in the foil, into large pan of cold water to cover. Bring to a boil and boil the salami for 1 hour.
Remove salami from foil and drain thoroughly on paper toweling.
Chill well before slicing.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix ingredients together
(dough
will be stiff).
Take piece of dough size of walnut
and shape like a finger.
Place in sheet pan about 1-inch apart.
Bake
at
for 20 to 30 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while
hot.	Roll
a few at a time, so as not to break them.

title: mexican tea cakes
directions: In bowl, cream butter with 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat in vanilla, pecans and salt until mixture is combined.
Add flour; beat dough until it is combined.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese, Roka and English cheese together.
Add vinegar and garlic powder.
Roll into a ball.
Chill.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: amish crunchy popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, marshmallows, brown sugar and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until dissolved.
Add peanut butter. Stir; pour over popcorn.
Stir until evenly coated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into 9-inch buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: confetti biscuits
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the flour, baking powder and salt. Add eggs, milk and cheese. Mix until just blended. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix with mixer until thoroughly blended. Cover and chill overnight.
Shape into log and roll in finely chopped pecans. Garnish with parsley, if desired. Serve with crackers.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on a dish (spread thin).
On top, spread the cocktail sauce.
Drain the shrimp and spread the shrimp all over the top of the sauce.
That's it, very easy.

title: "turkey dressing"
directions: A speck makes 1/4 saltspoon.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Wash and drain cranberries.
Heat cranberries in water to boiling point and cook until soft.
Run through a sieve.
Add 2 cups of sugar, juice and grated rind of 2 oranges to pulp.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour into ice cube tray and slightly freeze.
Take out and beat until very light.
Return to tray and finish freezing.
Serve with main course as a side dish.
Serves 12.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into hot, greased skillet and bake in 400° oven until done.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Put ice cream in a mixing bowl and let sit until soft enough to stir. Stir whipped topping into softened ice cream until well blended. Pour filling into pie shell, cover and place in freezer until firm.

title: italian green beans(low in fat)
directions: Put the green beans in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with the dressing mix. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Pour the water over beans and cover.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Delicious and easy!
Serves 6.

title: bandera ranch beans
directions: Clean beans and place into a kettle with 8 cups of water. Boil slowly for two hours until beans are tender.
Remove the floaters.
Using a large skillet, melt margarine and saute onions and green bell pepper until soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer slowly and stir for about 5 minutes.
Add to cooked beans and heat.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In Dutch oven or heavy pot, put oil and brown onion.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add roast beef and macaroni.
Put on low setting for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 8 people.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Boil zucchini and sugar hard for 6 minutes.
Add pineapple and lemon juice; boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in sterile jars and seal.
Makes 11 to 12 (8 ounce) jars.

title: baked beans
directions: Cube bacon and fry.
Save bacon grease and saute onions.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, garlic powder and mustard.
Drain all beans, add to mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Add Accent, salt and pepper.
Combine cheese, flour, crab meat and cream.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: honey mustard glaze for chicken
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; bring to boil for 1 minute. Stir the cornstarch and water together.
Combine both mixture; boil until thick.
Baste chicken while grilling.

title: bavarian sauerkraut
directions: Mix cabbage and sauerkraut together and layer it.
Put chopped onion and kolbasi on each layer and make 3 layers.
Pour tomato soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pound chicken and cut into thin strips.
Lightly coat with flour.
Heat in oil in large frying pan over medium-high heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan and set aside.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Heat butter in a skillet.
Add mushrooms to skillet and cook slowly, occasionally moving and turning gently with a spoon until mushrooms are tender and lightly browned.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Put in a warm dish and serve.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Brown meat, onion, pepper and celery.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In microwave dish, add cottage cheese and cooked pasta.
Microwave uncovered for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir a couple times, stir in cheeses.
Good and much easier than lasagna. Like it served with picante sauce.

title: super bran muffins
directions: Mix first three ingredients; set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Fill greased or papered muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare,
core
and
slice apples;
toss mixture of sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Turn into one 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with butter. Cover
with
other
9-inch
pie crust; seal and flute edge.
Cut slits
for escaping steam.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes and cashew bake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cashews, salt and ginger.
In 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, layer half the sweet potatoes, half peach slices, half brown sugar mix.
Repeat layers.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Spoon syrup over potatoes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, add all other ingredients except tortillas. Layer meat
sauce and tortillas.
Put cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gumdrop (ala viola hill)
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together; add eggs and flavorings. Mix dry ingredients alternately with pineapple juice.
Fold in tidbits, gumdrops and nuts.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ma's cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and shortening; mix well. Bake at 350°.

title: lobster tails
directions: Lift tail out of shell. Pour ingredients over meat in order. Add 1/2-inch of water to pan to keep meat moist. Bake at 500° for 1 minute per ounce.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl; beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans. Cover and chill.
Makes one 4-inch cheese ball.

title: sliced potato casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole. Slice potatoes with skins.
Layer potatoes, seasoned salt and Parmesan cheese.
Dot with oleo. Repeat layers until dish is full.
Add paprika for color. Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Very good warmed up. Warm up 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine, and cocoa together in sauce pan over medium heat. Bring to a full boil.
Boil for one minute, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: crab (or shrimp) mold
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Set aside.
Heat soup to boiling. Add cheese and thoroughly dissolve. Add gelatin and cool. Add mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Let thicken slightly. Add shredded crab or shrimp and pour into mold.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold. Serve with party rye or crackers.

title: french vanilla applesauce cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; turn out onto cake plate and drizzle with 3/4 cup powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon hot milk and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.

title: 7 layer cake
directions: Layer in baking dish the graham cracker crumb mixture.
Add chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips, then nuts, then coconut and then Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Wait 15 minutes to cool and cut.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Put vegetables in crock-pot in this order:
carrots, potatoes, onions, corn, 1 can tomatoes, hamburger and the second can of tomatoes.
The canned vegetables can be substituted with fresh vegetables.
Cook on low for approximately 8 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Brown onion.
Cook over medium heat. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Ready to use or can.
May add hot sauce to taste.

title: egg pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Combine egg, water and vinegar. Sprinkle over flour mixture, stirring lightly to form a ball. Wrap in waxed paper and chill at least 1 hour or until ready to use.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen pies.
Use dried apples or 2 cups mashed sweet potatoes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add molasses and egg; blend well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Then add water and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Saute onion in 1 teaspoon butter or oil. Add soups, salsa and Mexican cheese.
Mix with chicken. Top with crushed Doritos and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: one pan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well in nonstick 9 x 13-inch pan except cake mix.
Sprinkle cake mix over mixture.
Drizzle melted butter over top of cake mix.
Bake approximately 1 hour in 350° to 375° oven.

title: molded cranberry ring
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let stand.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add cold liquid.
Chill until partially set.
Add cranberry mixture, crushed pineapple, celery and walnuts.
Chill in large ring mold until firm.
Serves 12.

title: justin's zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil squash and onions for 10 minutes and drain well.
Mix together carrots, sour cream and soup.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Layer crumbs, squash, crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in layers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Heat 4 buns.
Spoon mixture onto buns.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil.
Mix in Jell-O. Slice strawberries in pie shell.
Pour Jell-O mixture over strawberries.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Shred lettuce into large ceramic bowl and toss with onion and an additional 1/2 to 1 cup sugar (to taste).
Bacon is best cooked in cast-iron skillet, do not drain fat.
To bacon add sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Cook until reaches boiling and then pour over lettuce and stir.
The hot liquid wilts lettuce.
Best served with Sunday dinner such as roast, mashed potatoes, green beans, etc.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, and Miracle Whip butter together and bring to a boil on low heat.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then take off stove and add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, and vanilla.
Also add as much peanut butter and pecans as you want. Pour into buttered pan and put into refrigerator and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: red snapper yucatan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet over medium heat, saute the onions, red pepper and olives.
Lay fish filets on top of sauteed onion, peppers and olives.
Add 3 tablespoons orange juice, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, and 1/4 teaspoon coriander.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
While fish is baking, mix a bit of cornstarch and water to thicken sauce.

title: raspberry-beet salad
directions: Heat 1 cup beet juice.
Mix jello into juice.
Add sweetener and vinegar.
Pour over beets.
Refrigerate; occasionally stir until set.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix together.
Put in ovenproof dish.
May top with pork chops, leftover roast or chicken.
Cook in oven for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pancake batter
directions: Beat all ingredients together, either by hand or electric mixer.
Cook on hot grill.
Makes 16 medium pancakes.

title: grannies doughnuts
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, egg and milk in a bowl.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together and stir into the sugar mixture.
Roll out on a floured surface and cut with a doughnut cutter.
Drop into deep, hot fat and fry until golden brown.
Drain and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: helen's country style ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put sauerkraut in Dutch oven and add salt and pepper.
Cover sauerkraut with water and cook for 1 hour. Add country style ribs to the sauerkraut; add water if needed. Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serve ribs and sauerkraut with mashed potatoes.

title: bonnie's easy cutout sugar cookies
directions: Cut together (like pie dough) the shortening, flour and salt. In a separate bowl, mix together the rest of ingredients; add this mixture to flour mixture.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except bananas and pecans.
Add mashed bananas and 1 cup pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, celery, pickles, pimiento, mayonnaise, salt, onion and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Mix well and chill. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in macaroni mixture.
Spoon into individual molds.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in 1 stick butter or oleo.
Add parsley flakes, onion tops, soup, shrimp, rice, bread and hot water.
Season to taste.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour into 2 quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and pats of butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan tassies
directions: You will need Wilton mini muffin pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together (except nuts).
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake at low temperature for about 40 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Beat well; pour over first layer.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream cheese and margarine together.
Add pepper to flour and cream into cheese mixture gradually.
Stir in Rice Krispies and nuts.
Chill, then roll into small balls and place on greased baking sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen quarter size cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni while browning hamburger meat.
Add tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup to hamburger meat.
Stir and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni to hamburger meat.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread small amount on each tortilla and roll up.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap and refrigerate. When ready to serve, slice each tortilla into 1 to 2-inch slices.

title: nanny's fruit cake
directions: Grease a loaf pan.
Line with wax paper and grease again. Place fruit and nuts in large bowl.
Sift flour and sugar over fruit.
Add beaten eggs with vanilla; mix well.
Pack in pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Use foil over top, if needed the last 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan. Remove wax paper.
Place in tinfoil and store in fridge.
Slice very thin to serve.

title: garbanzo oat waffles
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Let stand while waffle iron is heating.
Blend briefly again.
Pour into Pam-sprayed waffle iron and bake 8 to 12 minutes.
If waffle iron is hard to open, leave a few minutes longer.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Place ground beef, chili and onion (chopped) into pan.
Stir well and cook for 30 minutes on medium heat or until ground beef is completely cooked.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix and chill before serving.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In bowl, combine dry cake mix, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon. In 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish, spoon cherry pie filling into bottom.
Evenly sprinkle cake mix mixture over pie filling. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes or until topping is not doughy.
Turn once during cooking, if necessary.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pig stomach
directions: Soak pig stomach in salt water overnight and clean the stomach inside and out.
Mix other ingredients and stuff the stomach.
Bake at about 350° until it is nice and brown.
If you stick it once in a while, it will not break and the fat will run out.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine together until crumbly. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, nuts and baking powder.
Whip the eggs separately.
Make a well in the flour and add oil and eggs.
Mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken elegant
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add almonds.
Brown lightly.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Add soup and broth.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Defrost asparagus.
Grease a 2-quart casserole. Arrange chicken and asparagus in alternate layers.
Put sauce over.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve in patty shells or over toast points.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk.
Roll in flour (seasoned with salt and pepper).
Fry in hot oil over medium heat.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables and toss with oregano and Italian dressing. Marinate overnight.
One to 2 hours before serving, add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Serves 6 to 7 people.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Heat small amount of fat in a frying pan and drop by tablespoons.
Cook until brown on both sides.

title: graham cracker crisps
directions: Fill greased cookie sheet with separated graham crackers. Boil margarine, butter and sugar for 3 minutes on low.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Separate.
Cool on wax paper; do quickly.
If they become too hard, return to oven to soften.
Yields about 30.

title: bread pudding with rum sauce
directions: Break bread into pieces; soak in milk.
Mix well.
Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla, pineapple and raisins.
Pour over bread mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: harvest popcorn
directions: *1/3 cup unpopped corn makes about 2 1/2 quarts popped.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Make graham cracker pie crust.
Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch cake pan with crust.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar with cream cheese.
Mix Lucky Whip according to directions on box. Fold Lucky Whip into sugar mixture.
Pour into cake pan with pie crust.
Pour cherry pie mix on top.
Chill.
Serve in cakelike pieces.

title: spaghetti a la carbonara
directions: Prepare spaghetti al dente; drain.
Saute ham or Canadian bacon and onion in butter and white wine.
Put hot spaghetti, eggs, cheese, parsley and basil in warm serving bowl.
Mix well. Pour ham and sauce over spaghetti and mix again.
Serve with garlic bread.
Serves 6.

title: caramel nut ice cream
directions: Blend brown sugar, nuts and water.
Add Eagle Brand milk. Finish filling freezer with whole milk.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear into pieces the bread and place in greased baking pan. Brown and drain the sausage.
Place on top of the bread; sprinkle with the cheese.
Beat the eggs; add and beat the milk with the eggs.
Add the dry mustard, salt and pepper and beat.
Then pour over the sausage mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Cut into squares.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Bring to boil chicken, bamboo shoots and 2 cups broth. Dissolve cornstarch in 1 cup broth.
Add to boiling chicken.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add green pepper, celery and chestnuts. Cook 3 minutes, until crisp.
Add to chicken mixture.
Add soy sauce, mushrooms and ears of corn.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with nuts and noodles.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Can use oriental mixed vegetables and also use rice noodles (wonderful casserole).

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and gradually beat in well beaten eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Beat in salad dressing.
Toss together remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Place rice in shallow oven dish.
Brown pork chops and lay in rice.
Add liquid.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake for an additional 1/2 hour.

title: squash puppies
directions: Grate squash.
Add egg, onion and mix.
Add flour and most of meal.
It should be stiff enough to drop in oil and fry.
If the squash are real moist, you may not need the buttermilk.

title: frosting for banana cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla and continue beating until of spreading consistency.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, onion and egg.
Add enough milk to make a sticky dough.
Drop by rounded balls into deep fryer until brown.

title: salad delicious
directions: When Jell-O has cooled, add all ingredients and let set until congealed.
This is especially good served with a cottage or cream cheese dressing on lettuce.

title: festive shortbread cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar with hands until well blended. Add flour 1 cup at a time, mixing with hands until easy to handle and not sticky. Put through cookie press. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach delight pie
directions: Drain peach slices overnight on paper towels.
Fold sugar into sour cream.
Place alternate layers of peaches and sour cream in pie shell.
Chill several hours.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together in a 2 qt. pan, add milk and softened butter. Heat over medium heat until it comes to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: heavenly rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add to cooled milk.
Add all other ingredients, beating in flour, a cup or two at a time, until it sticks together.
Shape into round ball and cover.
Let rise twice its size, about 30 minutes.
Pour out onto floured surface and knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll out and cut with glass.
Dip into oil (in pan), fold in half, lining them close together.
Cook at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rosemary potato
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch pieces. Lay flat on cookie sheet. Sprinkle olive oil over potatoes.
Then lay rosemary and garlic salt and pepper.
Put into hot oven.
Turn as they get crispy. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meat delight
directions: Boil noodles; drain and set aside.
Chop and fry in butter onion, bell pepper and parsley.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add corn, cumin seed, tomato sauce, mushroom sauce and olives.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with noodles; put in baking dish.
Cover with cheese and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: french toast
directions: Heat margarine in a heavy skillet. Combine the egg, milk, vanilla and salt in a bowl; blend with a fork. Dip bread into egg mixture and saute in margarine on both sides to a golden brown. Sprinkle each with cinnsweet. Makes 6 servings.

title: christmas trees
directions: Cream the shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg, sifted dry ingredients, flavoring and a few drops of vegetable coloring.
Mix well.
Fill cookie press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheets, using the tree plate.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Place pretzels and butter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on top of cooled pretzels.
(The cream cheese mixture will spread better if you add a little of the Cool Whip with it.)
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of the cheese; chill. Next, dissolve jello in boiling water or juice.
Stir in berries and allow to thicken almost to jellied point.
Spread over topping and refrigerate.
(If you use your own strawberries and they have sugar in them, only use 3/4 cup sugar.)

title: hot taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with taco chips.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix in one bowl the flour, corn meal and sugar.
In another bowl mix milk and oil.
Pour into corn meal mix.
Dip hot dogs and fry.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix in cheeses; add tuna and green peas.
Pour into baking dish; cook in oven 10 to 15 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Instead of water, substitute milk. Pour batter into sheet cake pan, 13 x 9.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Take from oven and punch holes in top of cake with fork.
Mix cream of coconut oil and Eagle brand milk together. Put coconut on top of cake.
Pour milk mixture on top of this. Cool.
Frost with Cool Whip and coconut on top. Refrigerate. Enjoy!

title: oyster spread
directions: Mash oysters with a fork to make a paste.
Blend cream cheese and oysters until smooth.
Add lemon juice, onion, hot sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Chill 3 hours; roll in a ball and cover with chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: dressing for cabbage salad
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix until well blended. Pour over chopped cabbage.
Makes enough for 1 or 2 heads of cabbage.
Add carrots and peppers (chopped).

title: potato with apples and ham(jagaimo no ringoni)
directions: Rinse potatoes and put into microwave safe dish.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Peel.
Peel apples.
Soak in water for 5 minutes, then grate.
Put potatoes and bouillon cube into a pot and cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and add ham and grated apple.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add parsley and salt and pepper to taste before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Arrange Twinkies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine Jell-O and 3 cups boiling water.
Pour over Twinkies.
Slice strawberries on Twinkies.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and spread over all.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired.
Refrigerate until served.
Serves 12.

title: creamy tuna casserole(never any leftovers when i make this dish)
directions: Half-cook spaghetti - very al dente.
Set aside.
Saute mushrooms in olive oil with garlic clove, salt and pepper.
In electric blender, blend cream, butter, Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Add boiling water.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients slowly, mixing well. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with white frosting.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: Having cream cheese at room temperature, combine cheese, sauces, garlic powder and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Form into ball; roll in remainder of chopped nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt slightly to mix.
Stir in scalded milk.
Add corn.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° 45 to 50 minutes until a knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Soft center sets as it stands.

title: tyl's russian pork chops
directions: For Grill:
Place pork chops on foil.
Pour Russian dressing over pork chops.

Cut garlic gloves and put over pork chops. Cover pork chops with foil and grill for 1 hour at medium temperature. Or, oven bake pork chops for 30 minutes, pour off grease and pour Russian dressing over pork chops.
Add garlic and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: my oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Boil at a full rolling boil for exactly one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, cocoa and oats.
Mix well and quickly drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: blueberry salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch long cake pan, dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add blueberry pie filling. Stir, then add drained pineapple.
Stir, then set in refrigerator until jelled.
Cream cheese should be at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix together real good.
Put on top of jello and sprinkle pecan chips on top.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil chopped potatoes until fork-tender.
Cool.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl, except 1 egg (reserve it for top of potato salad).
Quarter or slice the 1 egg; sprinkle with paprika or pepper.

title: hog's head cheese
directions: In a large kettle, bring water to boil.
Add hog's head and boil for 3 hours.
Test with a fork to see if it can pull apart easily.
If not, continue to boil until tender.
Remove the heat from liquid.
Place on a large platter and remove the bones and skin.
Shred the meat, making sure all the bones have been removed.
Return shredded meat to kettle.
Chop onions, parsley, shallots and garlic finely.
Add to
kettle and boil 10 minutes. Add red pepper, black pepper and salt.
Boil 1 hour.
Pour into small glass bowls to serve.

title: red rice
directions: Fry onion and green pepper in oil until brown.
Add tomato paste.
Add sugar and mix.
Let tomato paste get a little dark and then add 3 cans (tomato paste size) of water.
Simmer.
Add 3 cups of rice and cook until all tomato sauce is absorbed.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, 1 cup sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla for 8 minutes.
Grease 9 inch pie plate.
Pour mixture in and bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 1 Tbsp sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Pour over cooling cake.
Return to oven for 10 minutes more.

title: chewies
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon well.
Pour into cake baking sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.
Remove; cut in squares while warm.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients.
May add celery seed.

title: quick corn bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and beat well.
Combine flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt. Add milk alternately with drys to egg mixture, mixing well after each addition. Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas(microwave easy)
directions: In a 2 quart casserole, heat chicken broth*.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, 1/4 cup taco sauce and chili peppers.
Spoon about 1/3 chicken mixture into center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon 3/4 cup taco sauce atop.
Cover dish with vented microwave safe plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until hot, turning dish half-turn every 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook covered, on High about 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
If desired, top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and ripe olives. Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: tangy barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat; add Tabasco and barbecue sauce and let simmer.
Add mustard, molasses and garlic to meat mixture while simmering. Saute onions and bell peppers until crunchy; add to meat mixture. Stir and put into casserole dish (do not cover).
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: angel's best marinated chicken
directions: Mix the ingredients in a large bowl; add chicken breasts, covering with marinade.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Cook on grill.

title: beef-noodle bake
directions: Saute ground beef with onions in skillet until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir in noodles.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: fat-free fried potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as normal to fry, slice as thin as possible. Spray Teflon skillet with Pam.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper to taste; cook on low heat until done.
Last few minutes, turn heat up to brown.

title: toffee candy
directions: Mix and cook to 300°.

Add 1/2 c. chopped nuts to cooked mixture and pour on a buttered cookie sheet. Melt 3 large chocolate bars and pour 1/2 over hardened candy. Sprinkle with nuts. When cool and hard turn over and pour rest of melted chocolate and sprinkle chopped nuts on other side. Break into chunks when cold.

title: pepperoni sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls in half and lay top aside. Spread with warmed pizza sauce.
Place pepperoni and cheese on top and spread with more sauce.
Place top on sandwich and microwave or place in warm oven until cheese is completely melted.

title: sandy's angel hair pasta
directions: Melt butter and saute garlic and onions.
Add crab.
Add cream and heat until slightly thickened.
Cook pasta and drain. Transfer to serving dish and pour sauce over.
Add cheese and toss thoroughly.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz and cream cheese together.
Place in microwave for 30 seconds.
Remove and beat with mixer until combined and creamy.
Add Worcestershire sauce and beat well.
Return to microwave and heat until bubbling hot.
Stir in crab meat or tuna. Use French bread cut into pieces to dip (any bread can be used).

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix and add hot milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes for double cake.

title: marbled pecan pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate with water and let cool.
Sift flour and salt and set aside.
Cream butter, shortening, cream cheese and sugar until very light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating with the flour mixture, beating on medium speed while adding.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Remove about 4 cups of batter and mix with the chocolate.
In a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan, layer the batter:
vanilla, chocolate, vanilla, chocolate and vanilla. Take a knife and reaching to the bottom, swirl through the batter to make marbled effect.
Sprinkle the chopped nuts on top and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done, beginning in a cold oven.

title: chicken ham casserole
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions.

Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with chicken and ham. In a bowl, combine the soup, milk, Colby cheese and pepper; pour over chicken mixture. Sprinkle with the Parmesan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt margarine in pan; add sugar and milk and blend well.
Add vanilla.
Bring to boil and boil 6 minutes (rolling boil).
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and 1 1/2 cups black walnuts, if desired.
Stir well.
Pour into a well-greased pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch and cool.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Brown sausage and onion together; drain.
Mix sausage, onion, kraut, parsley, garlic salt, bread crumbs and cream cheese. Chill.
After chilling, form into small balls.
Roll in flour. Dip in egg and milk mixture.
Roll in the cracker crumbs.
Fry until brown in hot grease.
Drain.
Happy New Year!
Makes approximately 36 balls.

title: annie's black chocolate cake
directions: Melt the chocolate. Add the butter and water.
Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Mix in flour sifter the sugar, salt, flour and baking soda.
Add these dry ingredients with the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla into the chocolate mixture.
Will be a thin batter, but this will make a moist, wonderful cake.
Bake at 375° until done.
This cake is baked in an angel food cake pan.

title: spinach balls #2
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine stuffing, onion, cheese and seasonings.
Mix together eggs, spinach and stuffing.
Pour melted butter over mixture and mix well.
Chill thoroughly and form into 1 inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
These can be frozen before baking. Do not thaw before baking frozen balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 48 appetizers.

title: rosalyn carter's cheese ring
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, nuts, onions and peppers; mix well. Press into 3-cup ring mold to make shape.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Remove from mold.
Fill center with strawberry preserves and serve with crackers.

title: fat-free banana muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain well.
Heat sauce, chicken and seasonings.
Spoon enough sauce to cover bottom of a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer half of the noodles, sauce and cheese. Repeat, ending with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crab cake casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Rinse and drain.
Cook onions and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, mustard and salt and cook until bubbly.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in lemon juice.
Clean crab meat.
Then mix with sauce and cottage cheese.
Fold in noodles.
Pour in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Microwave broccoli and margarine 8 minutes; stir.
Cook 4 minutes; cool completely.
Add corn meal mix, eggs, onion and cottage cheese.
Bake in greased Pyrex dish at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yam ring
directions: Mash hot yams in large bowl with milk, salt and pepper. Spread some of the butter (about 5 tablespoons) over bottom and side of a 6 1/2 cup ring mold.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Combine eggs, water, salad oil and pumpkin.
Add to dry ingredients and mix only until well blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: b.b.q. beef
directions: Mix ingredients, except meat, in a sauce pan and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until blended. Trim fat off meat and place in cooking pan. Pour the sauce
on top. Cover loosely. Bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: janette's kick-a-poo joy juice
directions: Combine orange juice, lemonade and apple juice.
Mix well. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice. Yields about 3 quarts.

title: carrot tzimmes
directions: Cook bones in water for at least 1 hour with salt, pepper and onion.
Skim fat off top.
Peel and slice carrots.
Peel and cut potatoes.
Add prunes and sugar to pot.
If Knaidlach are used, place on bottom of pot between bones in the liquid.
Then, add all vegetables.
Cover tightly and cook all together for at least 1 hour over low heat.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Note:
Add a little water if balls don't stick together.

title: zuke bread
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Sift and add the rest of the dry ingredients. Grease and flour two bread loaf pans. Divide the batter in the two pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: nancy's fabulous fudge
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
In a saucepan, melt chips (both kinds) over very low heat.
Stir in frosting, nuts and marshmallows.
Blend well, stirring constantly, until completely melted (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.

title: ez lasagna
directions: Combine tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes, spaghetti seasonings and mushrooms in saucepan.
Brown meat and diced onion.
Drain meat and combine with tomato sauce mixture.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash the beans well, removing any imperfect ones.
Place beans in cold water and soak overnight.
Boil 6 cups water.
Gradually add the beans to boiling water.
Simmer for 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Set aside to soak for 1 hour.
Then rinse beans and strain.

title: pozole
directions: Cook the chicken breasts.
Add salt to the hominy, garlic and onion. When the chicken is cooked, shred it.
Soak the chilies for 20 minutes. Press them through a strainer to remove the seeds and tough skin.
Add the chicken and hominy. Cook to a boil on the top of the stove. Slice the lettuce finely and serve the pozole with the lettuce and chips.

title: sesame cucumber salad
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in small saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Cover over medium heat, stirring constantly until
mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Cool completely.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples in rectangular baking dish.
(I use Granny Smith apples.)
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a small bowl.
With a fork, stir together the oil and the egg.
Mix in with the dry ingredients.
Spread over the apples. Sprinkle the cinnamon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas 1/2-inch thick, put lemon juice over them and set
aside.
Pour juice from fruit, saving 1 cup of juice. Follow instant pudding directions, adding fruit juice instead of milk.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Butter a 1 1/4
quart baking sheet.
Arrange a layer of apples on bottom, top with one half of the bread cubes and one half of the sugar.
Add a layer of apples, then the remaining bread cubes and the remaining apples.
Top with the rest of the sugar, sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Pour over hot water.
Cover and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: deluxe stuffed green peppers(really good!)
directions: I found the same old recipes in all my normal books, so let's do it different!

title: party punch
directions: Mix orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice; mix well. Pour in Ginger Ale, then add sherbet. Serves 40 people.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, mix together all the ingredients, except the Kisses.
Shape dough into 1 teaspoon balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Top with Kisses.

title: quail sandwich
directions: Place potato between two quail breasts.
Secure with toothpicks.
Wrap bacon strips around potato and breasts.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until potato is done. Cut into slices.
Great for kids to help with.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake according to package directions, except add pineapple juice that was drained from crushed pineapple.
When partially chilled, top with chilled crushed pineapple and return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan layer the pecans and coconut.
Mix the cake mix according to package directions and pour over the pecans and coconut.
Mix together the cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Check after 45 minutes.)

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and margarine together until creamy.
Roll into small balls the size of buckeyes.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler with a little paraffin wax.
