Using toothpick, dip peanut butter balls into chocolate mixture, being very careful not to cover entire ball. Makes approximately 100 balls.
Keep in cool place.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut up a chicken.
Soak the pieces in a bowl of milk, seasoned with salt and pepper, about 1/2 hour.
Then dredge the chicken in flour and fry in hot grease.

title: red lobster cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dough well.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine butter and garlic.
Brush over warm biscuits.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugars.
Gradually add egg; sift flour, salt and soda.
Add flour in 2 parts.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Save meat juice from a roast.
Blend eggs, flour, milk and salt.
This batter will be thin.
Pour meat juice into muffin tin large enough for 12 muffins.
Warm pan and meat juice in oven. Pour thin batter over top of each muffin cup.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until they are golden brown.
Serve standing around the roast on platter.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut cheese slices in half.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs and mix.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer all ingredients, ending with bread crumbs on top (2 to 3 layers each). Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover if it looks like it will boil over.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread a thin layer of cream cheese on a dinner plate about 1/4-inch thick. Pour cocktail sauce over top of cream cheese. Chop crab over top of while plate. Serve with crackers.

title: spicy baked chicken
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, parsley, Italian seasoning, salt and ground red pepper.
Put flour in a plastic bag. Place milk in a shallow bowl.
One at a time, put chicken pieces in the bag and shake to coat.
Dip in milk and then into crumb mixture, pressing lightly to coat well.
Place chicken pieces in a baking dish lined with nonstick spray.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serves 4.

title: crab dip appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients; heat and serve with herb toast.

title: meat loaf with a twist
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in the hamburger.
Form into a loaf in a large bread pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and place in oven for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.
Take off aluminum foil and let brown in oven for 10 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until sides separate from pan.

title: pillau(rice pudding)
directions: Brown onions lightly in melted butter.
Add rice, stirring constantly until the rice absorbs the butter.
Add raisins, almonds and all other ingredients except saffron.
Add just enough water to cover the mixture, then cover the pan and allow to simmer over a low flame until rice is tender.
When rice is almost done, add saffron.
Pour mixture into a buttered baking dish and place into an oven for about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature to soften.
Cream the cheese and gradually stir in crushed pineapple.
When smooth, add remaining ingredients, reserving 1 cup pecans.
Chill mixture well.
Form into ball and roll in remaining cup of pecans.
Chill until serving time.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Hull and wash fresh strawberries.
Slice into halves.
Combine 7-Up, cornstarch, sugar and food coloring, stirring until smooth. Cook until thick.
Cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour filling into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate until cold.
Top with whipped cream or dessert topping before serving.

title: annie's yummy jello dessert
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions. Chill until almost firm. Add drained, frozen strawberries and stir to mix. Top with marshmallows. Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil and sifted dry ingredients.
Combine with sugar, eggs and oil.
Add carrots, pineapple and pecans. Bake at 350° approximately 50 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain fruit thoroughly and heat the juice.
Dissolve Jell-O in the hot liquid.
Cool.
Mix with cottage cheese, fruit and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into mold or 8 x 12-inch dish. Chill until set.
Serves 8.

title: lo-cal eggnog
directions: Blend egg substitute on medium speed for one minute.
Add liquid sweetener, vanilla and one can evaporated milk.
Blend for one minute.
Add 1 can evaporated milk, 3 cups skim milk and 1 tablespoon brandy extract.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill 24 hours. One 8 ounce serving = 72 calories and 1/2 g. fat.

title: chewy dough
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, well greased and dusted with flour. Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
(Don't overcook or they won't be chewy.)

title: fresh sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes; bake in preheated 350° oven 40 minutes. Or, boil in water to cover for 20 minutes until soft.
Cool, peel and mash until smooth.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix wet ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together; shape into balls about golf ball size.
Chill 2 hours.

title: stew
directions: Brown meat in big pot.
Place potatoes, carrot pieces, cabbage, squash and corncob pieces on top of meat.
Cover all with water.
Boil until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Serve on plate one piece of meat, one potato, piece of cabbage, piece of squash, corn, piece of carrot and one serving of rice.
Add some broth to the mayonnaise.
This will serve as a sauce.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Single layer the chicken breasts in pan.
Mix ingredients. Spread marinade sauce onto breasts.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours, up to 3 days.
Grill 5 minutes on each side.

title: perfection salad
directions: Add to gelatin mixture and chill until firm.
Recipe is from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: hungarian keifleys
directions: Mix flour and butter together, then add rest of ingredients. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Roll a little dough at a time. Cut in squares and fill each square with about 1/2 teaspoon mixture.

title: pudding
directions: Pour mix into bowl.
Pour 2 cups of milk in bowl, too.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Mix around with spoon.
Serve.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Heat fruit in its syrup with 1/3 cup sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into pan, then pour fruit over the batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Heat sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to rolling boil.
Add peanuts.
Stir constantly.
Cook slowly until peanuts are golden brown and syrup spins a thread.
Remove from heat when syrup reaches 293°.
Add baking soda.
Beat rapidly then pour on buttered surface to cool.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: white buns
directions: Stir together all ingredients but only 2 cups sugar.
Stir well, then add additional flour.
As dough gets stiffer, knead in remaining flour.
Let raise twice after kneading well.
Form into buns.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Slice apples and combine with soda, vanilla and hot water.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and spices.
Sift in flour and salt.
Combine both mixtures.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake.
Serve warm or cold, topped with whipped cream.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and cocoa.
Remove from heat. Stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased cake size pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best punch ever
directions: Prepare day in advance.
Mix strawberries, vodka, lemon juice, orange juice concentrate and water.
Store, uncovered, in refrigerator overnight.
Pour cold mixture over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Stir in ginger ale gently.
Garnish punch with mint sprigs. Yield:
28 to 32 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook yellow layer in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar with pineapple (syrup included).
Pour over hot cake.
Make pudding as directed.
Pour over pineapple.
Put Cool Whip over the pudding mix.
Top with coconut and pecans, if desired.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Spread oats on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Toss with brown sugar, nuts and 1/2 stick butter.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Refrigerate.

title: cinnamon pull apart rolls
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Melt oleo and mix in sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Roll frozen rolls in oleo mixture.
Place in pan.
Pour remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture over rolls.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, bake 30 minutes at 350°. Do not fill pan too full or rolls will rise up and over the sides of the pan.

title: ham brown greasy gravy
directions: Put a little grease in skillet, fry sliced ham until brown on both sides.
When done, remove ham from skillet, then add the coffee and water to the ham grease, stir until all little pieces of ham are mixed with the liquid.
Pour in bowl.
Very good to put on biscuits, mashed potatoes, good on about anything.
I used to make lots of this, when we had our own ham meat.

title: seminary soup
directions: Cube meat and brown with onions.
Slice carrots, thin, cube potatoes and chop celery.
Place all, except cabbage, in kettle. Bring to a boil and simmer about 2 hours.
About 45 minutes before soup is done, add cabbage and seasoning.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie(yields 56 portions - 7 pies)
directions: Make pastry.
Line 7 (9-inch) pie pans.
Flute edges.
Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Combine sugars and seasonings; add to pumpkin mixture.
Add milk and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shells, 1 quart per pie.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean.

title: yellow sponge cake(a cake for using yolks after making an angel food cake)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt 3 times.
Beat until light the egg yolks.
Beat in gradually the white sugar, lemon, vanilla and cold water.
Add flour mixture gradually.
Bake in tube pan at 350°.

title: chili(microwave)
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and celery in a 3-quart casserole. Microwave at High for 6 to 9 minutes or until meat is cooked and vegetables are tender.
Drain fat and break up meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Microwave at High for 5 minutes. Stir.
Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes, stirring twice.

title: succotash
directions: Prepare corn and lima beans separate as package directs. Mix together. Drain. Smother onions; drain and add to mixture. Add butter and season with salt and pepper (seasoned to taste).

title: party slush
directions: In large punch bowl, pour in fruit punch and spoon in sherbet. Add liquid slowly.
*Use appropriate colors to match color scheme.

title: crunch top sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, whipped topping, powdered sugar, softened cream cheese and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into Coconut Crust.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well. Sprinkle over pie.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl mix graham cracker crumbs and butter with 2 tablespoons sugar, press mixture onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan or 2-quart casserole dish.
Chill in freezer while preparing filling.
In mixing bowl beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth, beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch until blended.
Stir in sour cream and pour into crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 200° and bake 45 minutes.
Turn off oven and allow to cool with oven door closed for 3 hours and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: granny's sausage gravy
directions: Slice sausage into 1/2-inch round slices.
Cook until done. Remove sausage from pan, reserving drippings.
In same pan used to fry sausage, heat sausage drippings on medium/high heat.
Stir flour in, 1 tablespoon at a time, until mixture resembles a thick paste. Mix together evaporated milk and water.
Pour slowly into pan, stirring constantly with a fork until completely cooked down to consistency of gravy.
Add pepper to taste.
Serve immediately over hot biscuits.

title: chicken casseroles out of cans
directions: Mix together all cans, mayonnaise and mustard.
Put the cooked potatoes in baking dish.
Layer the top with the chicken and put the cheese on top.
Cook 10 minutes.
If in oven, bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar. Press in ungreased baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour over baked layer. Bake until no indentation remains when touched in center, about 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 4 dozen squares.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Cook meat until it falls apart.
Mix the other ingredients and add to chopped meat.
Simmer for 1/2 hour and serve on buns.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spoon in muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter snacking cups
directions: Line 12-cup muffin pan with paper baking cups.
Combine crumbs and butter; mix well.
Press about 1 tablespoon of the crumb mixture into each cup.
Top each with about 1 tablespoon of the whipped topping.
Gradually add milk to peanut butter in bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in remaining whipped topping.
spoon into crumb-lined cups.
Top each cup with 1 teaspoon of the preserves.
Freeze about 4 hours.
To serve, peel off papers.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Prepare hot roll mix as directed on package, cut in 4 equal parts.
Roll each part out, brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with pepperoni and grated cheese and roll into balls.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 360° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with Pam.
Saute onion (and mushrooms) in nonstick skillet, until tender (I cook the chicken at the same time).
Combine broccoli, chicken, cheese and onion (and mushrooms) and spread evenly over the bottom of the pie plate.
In blender or food processor, blend Bisquick, eggs, milk, mustard, thyme, pepper (and salt).
Pour over chicken mixture. Bake in 400° oven 30 to 35 minutes, until browned on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ten bean soup
directions: Wash thoroughly the beans and place in a large kettle.
Cover with water.
Add salt and soak overnight.
In the a.m. (morning), drain.
Add 2 quarts of water and ham hocks.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Then add onion, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice, celery stalk and salt and pepper.
Simmer another 30 minutes.
Will serve 12.
Better if made a day or two ahead.

title: granny's cookies
directions: Spray square pan with oil spray.
Melt margarine and add 1 egg and the cake mix.
Blend until well mixed.
Pat dough ball in pan. For second layer, heat cream cheese until soft, being careful not to burn.
Blend 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar. Beat well.
Pour over cake.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Spread center of 20-inch sheet of heavy foil with butter.
Cut steak into serving portions.
Arrange on foil, slightly overlapping each portion.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix tomato juice and A.1. steak sauce and pour over meat.
Bring foil up over and fold edges to seal tightly.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Roll back foil and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: morning mix-up
directions: In a large skillet, brown potatoes in oil and add browned sausage and onions.
In small bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper. Add to the skillet.
Cook until eggs are set.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese.
Serve with sprinkled chives.

title: muffins
directions: Mix egg, milk and oil lightly with fork (Do Not overbeat). Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix carefully and place in greased, large muffin cups.
Makes 6 or 12 small ones.

title: creme de menthe salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix creme de menthe and pineapple juice.
Add to jello.
Cool until slightly thickened. Beat until frothy.
Fold in Cool Whip and drained pineapple. Refrigerate.

title: fruit fizz
directions: Chill all ingredients. Combine first 3 ingredients. Add ginger ale. Serve cold.

title: herb butter
directions: Cream the ingredients together.
Great on French bread and with Italian dishes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt cheese in medium saucepot.
Add soup, onion and wine; stir until smooth.
Layer broccoli in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Crush crackers and mix with butter/margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: deli's taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onion, celery, and bell pepper. Add taco seasoning when meat is done. Add cans of vegetables, milk and cheese and simmer until done. Add small amount of water if it is too thick.

title: old fashioned coconut cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box. Bake 3 or 4 layers. Mix sugar and milk together and cook over medium heat for 30 minutes. Then add coconut and cook additional 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Spread between layers. Best if made a day or two before serving. Keep in refrigerator.

title: pork and rice chinese style
directions: Cook pork and rice in oil at moderate temperature, stirring constantly until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Add green pepper and green onions, stir and cook 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce and mix carefully.
Drain mushrooms, add with beaten eggs.
Cook slowly, stirring until eggs are cooked.
Cut tomatoes into strips, fold into mixture and cook for about 1 minute longer.

title: oriental meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Shape into loaf and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain off excess drippings.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Bake in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (or until knife, when inserted, comes out clean).

title: chocolate upside down cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add butter, milk, pecans and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes.
Pour in greased pan.
Mix sugar and 1 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over cake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: crabmeat imperial
directions: Clean any shells out of crabmeat.
Mince green pepper very fine; stir in 2 tablespoons mayo.
May add a small amount extra until texture is moist.
Place in quiche plate.
Sprinkle lightly with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: perfection cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; stir in cold water and lemon juice.
Divide in half.
Chill one-half until syrupy; keep other half at room temperature for later.
Fold vegetables into syrupy gelatin; pour into 8-cup mold and chill until firm.
Chill second half of gelatin until syrupy; fold in cottage cheese combined with grated onion and salt.
Spoon over chilled layer in mold; chill until firm.
Unmold onto platter; garnish with radish roses and water cress.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; set aside.
Cut broccoli into florets and combine in a large bowl with cheese and bacon.
Toss with mayonnaise dressing.
Cover and chill overnight before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: unbaked fruitcake
directions: Dissolve vanilla wafers in milk.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pack in container.
Let set until next day.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in broth until real moist.
Make into patties.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn over after 8 minutes if so desired.

title: apricot lamb
directions: Trim lamb and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Thread onto bamboo skewers.
Mix ingredients in a glass dish.
Add lamb and turn to coat. Marinate for 1 hour, turning occasionally.

title: fruit soup from trondheim(trondheimsuppe)
directions: In a thick-bottomed kettle, bring water to a boil.
Add rice and cook 1/2 hour, stirring constantly.
Add raisins and cook another 15 minutes.
Make a paste of the flour, cream and lemon juice.
Add paste to the soup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add fruit juice.
Serve as a dinner dessert.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased casserole.
Top with more cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, slice enough apples to cover bottom twice.
Sprinkle sugar over apples and add water.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over apples and slice margarine over the cake mix. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: a cool and delicious cake
directions: Bake the cake in two layers, according to directions.
Cool and split each layer horizontally.
On each layer spread Cool Whip, coconut and walnuts.
On top layer, add chocolate chips to the toppings.
Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread; let cool, then crumble.
Add the crumbled bacon, eggs, green pepper and onion.
Put tomatoes in last.
Add mayonnaise and stir.
Chill until served.
Better next day if some left over.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; gradually add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.

title: alexander cocktail
directions: Shake well with cracked ice and strain into 4 ounce cocktail glass.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Cream margarine and pour over peanut butter in big bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla until mixture forms large ball.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip each ball into chocolate.
Cool on wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Chop corned beef in food processor and add the cream cheese and the rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: lime jello mist
directions: You will need 1 (9 x 9-inch) mold or Bundt cake pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave in oven for 1 hour.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and store in an airtight container.
Use 2 tablespoons of mix per cup of water.

title: apple squares
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl and cut in shortening.
Combine egg and 2 tablespoons water.
Mix with flour mixture until moistened.
Roll out 1/2 dough and pat in pan.
Fill with apples. Combine sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Blend in 1 cup water and cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Pour over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place rolled dough over top, sealing edges.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost when nearly cool.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
(Great for chicken).

title: tuna casserole
directions: Crush chips and mix all together. Bake in casserole dish at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add the next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: basic chinese meat marinade
directions: Mix and pour over presliced meat. Let stand 10 to 20 minutes or longer. You are ready to cook.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes.
Place potatoes and onions in saucepan with milk.
Bring to boil and gently simmer about 10 minutes, stirring several times to prevent sticking.
Generously butter a baking dish.
Put half of potatoes and onions in bottom. Sprinkle half of cheese over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put rest of potatoes over cheese, then follow with rest of cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour enough hot milk over cheese that you can see surface of milk through the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese crabmeat dreams
directions: Mix together until smooth; add crab.
Spread on muffins, then cut in fourths.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Put under broiler 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve.
Good.

title: pat's heavenly hash
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and milk in a large saucepan. Add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix until well coated.
Pour into wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill 2 hours.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add eggs and blend.
Then add dry ingredients.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Stir together dressing, jam and soup mix. Pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees until tender (about 1 hour). Serve over rice. Serves 8.

title: chicken in soy sauce
directions: Garlic chicken; set aside for 10 minutes. Saute onion in oil, then add chicken. Fry chicken until brown on outside. Remove oil and add soy sauce and water. Cover and cook for about 45 minutes on medium.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, brown sugar, and vanilla. Stir until creamy.

title: peach halves
directions: Put peach halves in baking dish.
Put marmalade in center of each half, top with nutmeg, heat through in oven.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and peanut morsels in 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time. Blend well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spoon on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Store in airtight container (very good).

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and pineapple.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir melted butter with bread cubes. Put into liquid mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
(This is great served with ham.)

title: cranberry party punch
directions: Combine just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; add half and half, then vinegar and butter.
Put on stove, stirring constantly, over medium heat. Bring to a boil, cook and stir until thick.
If it gets too stiff, add a little more half and half.
Add vanilla and cool.
Crush or leave nuts whole.
Slice bananas.
Layer bananas, syrup and nuts. Repeat until all is used.

title: low-fat vegetable dip
directions: Mix well to combine and refrigerate.
Serve chilled with raw vegetables.
Makes 1 pint.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower and onion in 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Mix other ingredients except bacon.
Spoon onto layers. Sprinkle bacon over dressing.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add soups and water to beef in skillet.
Bring to boil.
Put rice in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, covered.
Pour beef mixture over rice. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: coffeecake
directions: Stir butter to soften; add sugar and cream till fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating smooth after each addition.
Pour into greased 9x9x2-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, sprinkle over batter.
Bake in moderate oven (375) 25-30 minutes or till done.
Cool 15 minutes; cut in squares and serve warm.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt.
Add water.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Makes two 9-inch pie shells.

title: snicker apple salad
directions: Cut apples into chunks.
Cut Snickers candy bar into pieces. Add Cool Whip and mix.
Can be used as a dessert.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix salt and pepper with ground beef and make into very small meatballs.
Brown in frying pan and drain the excess fat.
Combine the catsup and Coca-Cola and stir well.
Then cover the meatballs with the liquid and cook over medium heat until thickened, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange delite salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill before serving.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo in pan.
Pour mixture of sugar, flour and milk over oleo.
Add drained peaches.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Place in greased muffin tin.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in cream, cheese and egg yolk.
Pour sauce over pasta; toss to coat well.

title: cello chicken
directions: Start with tortillas layered in the bottom of a baking dish. Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Second, layer chicken mixture, then third layer of cheese.
Repeat until all is in layers.
End with cheese on the top.
Arrange sliced black olives in an attractive pattern on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add zucchini with spoon.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Put 6 ounce package of chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dip
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seeds in 300° oven for 10 minutes. Break up Ramen noodles.
Add everything together.
Let stand 2 hours or overnight.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until they just begin to brown (do not overcook).
Cool on wire rack.

title: grandma's candy apples
directions: In sauce pan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup & salt. Cook over medium heat; stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil (10 to 12 minutes).

Stir in sweetened condensed milk. Continue cooking; stirring occasionally, until candy thermometer reaches 245 degrees or small amount of mixture dropped into ice water forms into a firm ball (20 to 25 minutes).
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Dip apples in caramel mixture.
Dip end of apples into chopped peanuts.
Place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm (10 minutes).

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, mix the water, rice, tomatoes, cheese spread, onion, garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning.
Top the mixture with the chicken pieces/breasts and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Use High power.
Cook brown sugar, corn syrup and margarine for 5 minutes, stirring every minute.
Add cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir well!
Pour over popcorn in a brown grocery bag.
Cook 1 minute.
Shake it up.
Cook 1 more minute and shake.
Cook about 30 seconds and shake.
Cook 30 seconds more and shake.
Spread on cookie sheet.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Dry mushrooms.
Saute in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Dissolve cubes in hot water in casserole.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and blend with flour.
Add cream, salt and pepper. Pour mixture into casserole.
Add mushrooms.
Top with cheese and crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container.

title: african one pot meal-american style
directions: Use a
casserole dish with lid. Spray Pam on inside of dish. Mix vegetables and place in dish first, then add stock. Place chicken pieces on top. Cover dish with lid.

title: barbecued spare ribs
directions: Put ribs in roasting pan.
Slice onions over top of ribs.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add cream with egg mixture.
Mix together.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: p-nut butter-ice cream pies
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut butter together. Spread into ready made crusts.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Divide into 4 portions.
Roll each into ball.
Shake in bag with cornflake crumbs until well covered.
Pinch top of ball and flatten bottom so that it will be in the form of croquette (slightly cone shape).
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Make ahead and refrigerate to save time.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed vidalia onions
directions: Peel and wash onions.
Simmer in enough water to cover onions for 10 mins. until almost tender.
Remove pulp leaving only 2 outside
layers of onions.
Add pulp to other ingredients and place in blender on 'mix' setting for 10 seconds.
Place onion shells in lightly oiled muffin tins.
Fill with stuffing, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on 325°
for about 30 min.
To serve: place around meat dish.
Only very sweet onions work for this recipe. Serves 6.

title: chicken spaghetti(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Boil chicken in water (not too much water).
Last 10 to 15 minutes, add celery, onions and bell pepper.
Remove chicken; debone.
(Keep chicken broth.)
Add parsley and cubed chicken meat. Remove spaghetti from burner.
Stir diced cheese into spaghetti.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in boiling water in skillet. Add butter and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add sweet potatoes; cook over medium heat, about 15 minutes, basting frequently.
When syrup thickens and is glossy, remove from heat. Serve hot.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: fast yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine. Cool until lukewarm. Put water in warm bowl (large) and sprinkle yeast over water; stir until dissolved.
Add milk; mix egg, 2 cups flour and beat until smooth. Stir in enough flour to make soft dough. Cover and let rise, about 30 minutes. Punch down. Make

in 2 dozen rolls or divide into 4 pieces on a greased pie plate for sub rolls or add 2 cups raisins for raisin bread. Let rise 30 minutes. Grease pans bread is to be baked in. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Combine margarine and cheese.
Stir over medium heat until melted.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and cereal.
Let cool slightly.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute vegetables in small amount of oil until soft.
Add can of stewed tomatoes, bouillon, water, 1 bay leaf, rice and shrimp. Cook briskly for 20 minutes, then add crab meat and black pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: mexican chocolate wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine brown sugar and butter.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until light and fluffy.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Continue beating, scraping bowl often, until well mixed.
Reduce speed to low.
